131void NoteKeyProtocolAndMedia(KeyExchangeProtocolType protocol_type,
132 cricket::MediaType media_type) {
133 // Array of structs needed to map {KeyExchangeProtocolType,
134 // cricket::MediaType} to KeyExchangeProtocolMedia without using std::map in
135 // order to avoid -Wglobal-constructors and -Wexit-time-destructors.
136 static constexpr struct {
137 KeyExchangeProtocolType protocol_type;
138 cricket::MediaType media_type;
139 KeyExchangeProtocolMedia protocol_media;
140 } kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaMap[] = {
141 {kEnumCounterKeyProtocolDtls, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
142 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeDtlsAudio},
143 {kEnumCounterKeyProtocolDtls, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO,
144 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeDtlsVideo},
145 {kEnumCounterKeyProtocolDtls, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA,
146 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeDtlsData},
147 {kEnumCounterKeyProtocolSdes, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
148 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeSdesAudio},
149 {kEnumCounterKeyProtocolSdes, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO,
150 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeSdesVideo},
151 {kEnumCounterKeyProtocolSdes, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA,
152 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeSdesData},
153 };
154
155 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.KeyProtocol", protocol_type,
156 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMax);
157
158 for (const auto& i : kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaMap) {
159 if (i.protocol_type == protocol_type && i.media_type == media_type) {
160 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.KeyProtocolByMedia",
161 i.protocol_media,
162 kEnumCounterKeyProtocolMediaTypeMax);
163 }
164 }
165}

167std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*> GetBundleGroupsByMid(
168 const SessionDescription* desc) {
169 std::vector<const cricket::ContentGroup*> bundle_groups =
170 desc->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
171 std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*> bundle_groups_by_mid;
172 for (const cricket::ContentGroup* bundle_group : bundle_groups) {
173 for (const std::string& content_name : bundle_group->content_names()) {
174 bundle_groups_by_mid[content_name] = bundle_group;
175 }
176 }
177 return bundle_groups_by_mid;
178}

180// Returns true if |new_desc| requests an ICE restart (i.e., new ufrag/pwd).
181bool CheckForRemoteIceRestart(const SessionDescriptionInterface* old_desc,
182 const SessionDescriptionInterface* new_desc,
183 const std::string& content_name) {
184 if (!old_desc) {
185 return false;
186 }
187 const SessionDescription* new_sd = new_desc->description();
188 const SessionDescription* old_sd = old_desc->description();
189 const ContentInfo* cinfo = new_sd->GetContentByName(content_name);
190 if (!cinfo || cinfo->rejected) {
191 return false;
192 }
193 // If the content isn't rejected, check if ufrag and password has changed.
194 const cricket::TransportDescription* new_transport_desc =
195 new_sd->GetTransportDescriptionByName(content_name);
196 const cricket::TransportDescription* old_transport_desc =
197 old_sd->GetTransportDescriptionByName(content_name);
198 if (!new_transport_desc || !old_transport_desc) {
199 // No transport description exists. This is not an ICE restart.
200 return false;
201 }
202 if (cricket::IceCredentialsChanged(
203 old_transport_desc->ice_ufrag, old_transport_desc->ice_pwd,
204 new_transport_desc->ice_ufrag, new_transport_desc->ice_pwd)) {
205 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Remote peer requests ICE restart for " << content_name
206 << ".";
207 return true;
208 }
209 return false;
210}

234void ReportSimulcastApiVersion(const char* name,
235 const SessionDescription& session) {
236 bool has_legacy = false;
237 bool has_spec_compliant = false;
238 for (const ContentInfo& content : session.contents()) {
239 if (!content.media_description()) {
240 continue;
241 }
242 has_spec_compliant |= content.media_description()->HasSimulcast();
243 for (const StreamParams& sp : content.media_description()->streams()) {
244 has_legacy |= sp.has_ssrc_group(cricket::kSimSsrcGroupSemantics);
245 }
246 }
247
248 if (has_legacy) {
249 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(name, kSimulcastApiVersionLegacy,
250 kSimulcastApiVersionMax);
251 }
252 if (has_spec_compliant) {
253 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(name, kSimulcastApiVersionSpecCompliant,
254 kSimulcastApiVersionMax);
255 }
256 if (!has_legacy && !has_spec_compliant) {
257 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(name, kSimulcastApiVersionNone,
258 kSimulcastApiVersionMax);
259 }
260}

281// Logic to decide if an m= section can be recycled. This means that the new
282// m= section is not rejected, but the old local or remote m= section is
283// rejected. |old_content_one| and |old_content_two| refer to the m= section
284// of the old remote and old local descriptions in no particular order.
285// We need to check both the old local and remote because either
286// could be the most current from the latest negotation.
287bool IsMediaSectionBeingRecycled(SdpType type,
288 const ContentInfo& content,
289 const ContentInfo* old_content_one,
290 const ContentInfo* old_content_two) {
291 return type == SdpType::kOffer && !content.rejected &&
292 ((old_content_one && old_content_one->rejected) ||
293 (old_content_two && old_content_two->rejected));
294}
295
296// Verify that the order of media sections in |new_desc| matches
297// |current_desc|. The number of m= sections in |new_desc| should be no
298// less than |current_desc|. In the case of checking an answer's
299// |new_desc|, the |current_desc| is the last offer that was set as the
300// local or remote. In the case of checking an offer's |new_desc| we
301// check against the local and remote descriptions stored from the last
302// negotiation, because either of these could be the most up to date for
303// possible rejected m sections. These are the |current_desc| and
304// |secondary_current_desc|.
305bool MediaSectionsInSameOrder(const SessionDescription& current_desc,
306 const SessionDescription* secondary_current_desc,
307 const SessionDescription& new_desc,
308 const SdpType type) {
309 if (current_desc.contents().size() > new_desc.contents().size()) {
310 return false;
311 }
312
313 for (size_t i = 0; i < current_desc.contents().size(); ++i) {
314 const cricket::ContentInfo* secondary_content_info = nullptr;
315 if (secondary_current_desc &&
316 i < secondary_current_desc->contents().size()) {
317 secondary_content_info = &secondary_current_desc->contents()[i];
318 }
319 if (IsMediaSectionBeingRecycled(type, new_desc.contents()[i],
320 &current_desc.contents()[i],
321 secondary_content_info)) {
322 // For new offer descriptions, if the media section can be recycled, it's
323 // valid for the MID and media type to change.
324 continue;
325 }
326 if (new_desc.contents()[i].name != current_desc.contents()[i].name) {
327 return false;
328 }
329 const MediaContentDescription* new_desc_mdesc =
330 new_desc.contents()[i].media_description();
331 const MediaContentDescription* current_desc_mdesc =
332 current_desc.contents()[i].media_description();
333 if (new_desc_mdesc->type() != current_desc_mdesc->type()) {
334 return false;
335 }
336 }
337 return true;
338}

340bool MediaSectionsHaveSameCount(const SessionDescription& desc1,
341 const SessionDescription& desc2) {
342 return desc1.contents().size() == desc2.contents().size();
343}
344// Checks that each non-rejected content has SDES crypto keys or a DTLS
345// fingerprint, unless it's in a BUNDLE group, in which case only the
346// BUNDLE-tag section (first media section/description in the BUNDLE group)
347// needs a ufrag and pwd. Mismatches, such as replying with a DTLS fingerprint
348// to SDES keys, will be caught in JsepTransport negotiation, and backstopped
349// by Channel's |srtp_required| check.
350RTCError VerifyCrypto(const SessionDescription* desc,
351 bool dtls_enabled,
352 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
353 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
354 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info : desc->contents()) {
355 if (content_info.rejected) {
356 continue;
357 }
358 // Note what media is used with each crypto protocol, for all sections.
359 NoteKeyProtocolAndMedia(dtls_enabled ? webrtc::kEnumCounterKeyProtocolDtls
360 : webrtc::kEnumCounterKeyProtocolSdes,
361 content_info.media_description()->type());
362 const std::string& mid = content_info.name;
363 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(mid);
364 const cricket::ContentGroup* bundle =
365 it != bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
366 if (bundle && mid != *(bundle->FirstContentName())) {
367 // This isn't the first media section in the BUNDLE group, so it's not
368 // required to have crypto attributes, since only the crypto attributes
369 // from the first section actually get used.
370 continue;
371 }
372
373 // If the content isn't rejected or bundled into another m= section, crypto
374 // must be present.
375 const MediaContentDescription* media = content_info.media_description();
376 const TransportInfo* tinfo = desc->GetTransportInfoByName(mid);
377 if (!media || !tinfo) {
378 // Something is not right.
379 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, kInvalidSdp);
380 }
381 if (dtls_enabled) {
382 if (!tinfo->description.identity_fingerprint) {
383 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
384 << "Session description must have DTLS fingerprint if "
385 "DTLS enabled.";
386 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
387 kSdpWithoutDtlsFingerprint);
388 }
389 } else {
390 if (media->cryptos().empty()) {
391 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
392 << "Session description must have SDES when DTLS disabled.";
393 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, kSdpWithoutSdesCrypto);
394 }
395 }
396 }
397 return RTCError::OK();
398}

400// Checks that each non-rejected content has ice-ufrag and ice-pwd set, unless
401// it's in a BUNDLE group, in which case only the BUNDLE-tag section (first
402// media section/description in the BUNDLE group) needs a ufrag and pwd.
403bool VerifyIceUfragPwdPresent(
404 const SessionDescription* desc,
405 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
406 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
407 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info : desc->contents()) {
408 if (content_info.rejected) {
409 continue;
410 }
411 const std::string& mid = content_info.name;
412 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(mid);
413 const cricket::ContentGroup* bundle =
414 it != bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
415 if (bundle && mid != *(bundle->FirstContentName())) {
416 // This isn't the first media section in the BUNDLE group, so it's not
417 // required to have ufrag/password, since only the ufrag/password from
418 // the first section actually get used.
419 continue;
420 }
421
422 // If the content isn't rejected or bundled into another m= section,
423 // ice-ufrag and ice-pwd must be present.
424 const TransportInfo* tinfo = desc->GetTransportInfoByName(mid);
425 if (!tinfo) {
426 // Something is not right.
427 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << kInvalidSdp;
428 return false;
429 }
430 if (tinfo->description.ice_ufrag.empty() ||
431 tinfo->description.ice_pwd.empty()) {
432 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Session description must have ice ufrag and pwd.";
433 return false;
434 }
435 }
436 return true;
437}

439RTCError ValidateMids(const cricket::SessionDescription& description) {
440 std::set<std::string> mids;
441 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content : description.contents()) {
442 if (content.name.empty()) {
443 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
444 "A media section is missing a MID attribute.");
445 }
446 if (!mids.insert(content.name).second) {
447 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
448 "Duplicate a=mid value '" + content.name + "'.");
449 }
450 }
451 return RTCError::OK();
452}

466// Map internal signaling state name to spec name:
467// https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#rtcsignalingstate-enum
468std::string GetSignalingStateString(
469 PeerConnectionInterface::SignalingState state) {
470 switch (state) {
471 case PeerConnectionInterface::kStable:
472 return "stable";
473 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalOffer:
474 return "have-local-offer";
475 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalPrAnswer:
476 return "have-local-pranswer";
477 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemoteOffer:
478 return "have-remote-offer";
479 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemotePrAnswer:
480 return "have-remote-pranswer";
481 case PeerConnectionInterface::kClosed:
482 return "closed";
483 }
484 RTC_NOTREACHED();
485 return "";
486}

488// This method will extract any send encodings that were sent by the remote
489// connection. This is currently only relevant for Simulcast scenario (where
490// the number of layers may be communicated by the server).
491std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters> GetSendEncodingsFromRemoteDescription(
492 const MediaContentDescription& desc) {
493 if (!desc.HasSimulcast()) {
494 return {};
495 }
496 std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters> result;
497 const SimulcastDescription& simulcast = desc.simulcast_description();
498
499 // This is a remote description, the parameters we are after should appear
500 // as receive streams.
501 for (const auto& alternatives : simulcast.receive_layers()) {
502 RTC_DCHECK(!alternatives.empty());
503 // There is currently no way to specify or choose from alternatives.
504 // We will always use the first alternative, which is the most preferred.
505 const SimulcastLayer& layer = alternatives[0];
506 RtpEncodingParameters parameters;
507 parameters.rid = layer.rid;
508 parameters.active = !layer.is_paused;
509 result.push_back(parameters);
510 }
511
512 return result;
513}
514
515RTCError UpdateSimulcastLayerStatusInSender(
516 const std::vector<SimulcastLayer>& layers,
517 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal> sender) {
518 RTC_DCHECK(sender);
519 RtpParameters parameters = sender->GetParametersInternal();
520 std::vector<std::string> disabled_layers;
521
522 // The simulcast envelope cannot be changed, only the status of the streams.
523 // So we will iterate over the send encodings rather than the layers.
524 for (RtpEncodingParameters& encoding : parameters.encodings) {
525 auto iter = std::find_if(layers.begin(), layers.end(),
526 [&encoding](const SimulcastLayer& layer) {
527 return layer.rid == encoding.rid;
528 });
529 // A layer that cannot be found may have been removed by the remote party.
530 if (iter == layers.end()) {
531 disabled_layers.push_back(encoding.rid);
532 continue;
533 }
534
535 encoding.active = !iter->is_paused;
536 }
537
538 RTCError result = sender->SetParametersInternal(parameters);
539 if (result.ok()) {
540 result = sender->DisableEncodingLayers(disabled_layers);
541 }
542
543 return result;
544}
545
546bool SimulcastIsRejected(const ContentInfo* local_content,
547 const MediaContentDescription& answer_media_desc) {
548 bool simulcast_offered = local_content &&
549 local_content->media_description() &&
550 local_content->media_description()->HasSimulcast();
551 bool simulcast_answered = answer_media_desc.HasSimulcast();
552 bool rids_supported = RtpExtension::FindHeaderExtensionByUri(
553 answer_media_desc.rtp_header_extensions(), RtpExtension::kRidUri);
554 return simulcast_offered && (!simulcast_answered || !rids_supported);
555}
556
557RTCError DisableSimulcastInSender(
558 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal> sender) {
559 RTC_DCHECK(sender);
560 RtpParameters parameters = sender->GetParametersInternal();
561 if (parameters.encodings.size() <= 1) {
562 return RTCError::OK();
563 }
564
565 std::vector<std::string> disabled_layers;
566 std::transform(
567 parameters.encodings.begin() + 1, parameters.encodings.end(),
568 std::back_inserter(disabled_layers),
569 [](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) { return encoding.rid; });
570 return sender->DisableEncodingLayers(disabled_layers);
571}

590// Add options to |[audio/video]_media_description_options| from |senders|.
591void AddPlanBRtpSenderOptions(
592 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<
593 RtpSenderProxyWithInternal<RtpSenderInternal>>>& senders,
594 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions* audio_media_description_options,
595 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions* video_media_description_options,
596 int num_sim_layers) {
597 for (const auto& sender : senders) {
598 if (sender->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
599 if (audio_media_description_options) {
600 audio_media_description_options->AddAudioSender(
601 sender->id(), sender->internal()->stream_ids());
602 }
603 } else {
604 RTC_DCHECK(sender->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
605 if (video_media_description_options) {
606 video_media_description_options->AddVideoSender(
607 sender->id(), sender->internal()->stream_ids(), {},
608 SimulcastLayerList(), num_sim_layers);
609 }
610 }
611 }
612}
613
614cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForTransceiver(
615 RtpTransceiver* transceiver,
616 const std::string& mid,
617 bool is_create_offer) {
618 // NOTE: a stopping transceiver should be treated as a stopped one in
619 // createOffer as specified in
620 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#dom-rtcpeerconnection-createoffer.
621 bool stopped =
622 is_create_offer ? transceiver->stopping() : transceiver->stopped();
623 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions media_description_options(
624 transceiver->media_type(), mid, transceiver->direction(), stopped);
625 media_description_options.codec_preferences =
626 transceiver->codec_preferences();
627 media_description_options.header_extensions =
628 transceiver->HeaderExtensionsToOffer();
629 // This behavior is specified in JSEP. The gist is that:
630 // 1. The MSID is included if the RtpTransceiver's direction is sendonly or
631 // sendrecv.
632 // 2. If the MSID is included, then it must be included in any subsequent
633 // offer/answer exactly the same until the RtpTransceiver is stopped.
634 if (stopped || (!RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(transceiver->direction()) &&
635 !transceiver->has_ever_been_used_to_send())) {
636 return media_description_options;
637 }
638
639 cricket::SenderOptions sender_options;
640 sender_options.track_id = transceiver->sender()->id();
641 sender_options.stream_ids = transceiver->sender()->stream_ids();
642
643 // The following sets up RIDs and Simulcast.
644 // RIDs are included if Simulcast is requested or if any RID was specified.
645 RtpParameters send_parameters =
646 transceiver->sender_internal()->GetParametersInternal();
647 bool has_rids = std::any_of(send_parameters.encodings.begin(),
648 send_parameters.encodings.end(),
649 [](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) {
650 return !encoding.rid.empty();
651 });
652
653 std::vector<RidDescription> send_rids;
654 SimulcastLayerList send_layers;
655 for (const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding : send_parameters.encodings) {
656 if (encoding.rid.empty()) {
657 continue;
658 }
659 send_rids.push_back(RidDescription(encoding.rid, RidDirection::kSend));
660 send_layers.AddLayer(SimulcastLayer(encoding.rid, !encoding.active));
661 }
662
663 if (has_rids) {
664 sender_options.rids = send_rids;
665 }
666
667 sender_options.simulcast_layers = send_layers;
668 // When RIDs are configured, we must set num_sim_layers to 0 to.
669 // Otherwise, num_sim_layers must be 1 because either there is no
670 // simulcast, or simulcast is acheived by munging the SDP.
671 sender_options.num_sim_layers = has_rids ? 0 : 1;
672 media_description_options.sender_options.push_back(sender_options);
673
674 return media_description_options;
675}

739// Used by parameterless SetLocalDescription() to create an offer or answer.
740// Upon completion of creating the session description, SetLocalDescription() is
741// invoked with the result.
742class SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ImplicitCreateSessionDescriptionObserver
743 : public CreateSessionDescriptionObserver {
744 public:
745 ImplicitCreateSessionDescriptionObserver(
746 rtc::WeakPtr<SdpOfferAnswerHandler> sdp_handler,
747 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface>
748 set_local_description_observer)
749 : sdp_handler_(std::move(sdp_handler)),
750 set_local_description_observer_(
751 std::move(set_local_description_observer)) {}
752 ~ImplicitCreateSessionDescriptionObserver() override {
753 RTC_DCHECK(was_called_);
754 }
755
756 void SetOperationCompleteCallback(
757 std::function<void()> operation_complete_callback) {
758 operation_complete_callback_ = std::move(operation_complete_callback);
759 }
760
761 bool was_called() const { return was_called_; }
762
763 void OnSuccess(SessionDescriptionInterface* desc_ptr) override {
764 RTC_DCHECK(!was_called_);
765 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc(desc_ptr);
766 was_called_ = true;
767
768 // Abort early if |pc_| is no longer valid.
769 if (!sdp_handler_) {
770 operation_complete_callback_();
771 return;
772 }
773 // DoSetLocalDescription() is a synchronous operation that invokes
774 // |set_local_description_observer_| with the result.
775 sdp_handler_->DoSetLocalDescription(
776 std::move(desc), std::move(set_local_description_observer_));
777 operation_complete_callback_();
778 }
779
780 void OnFailure(RTCError error) override {
781 RTC_DCHECK(!was_called_);
782 was_called_ = true;
783 set_local_description_observer_->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(RTCError(
784 error.type(), std::string("SetLocalDescription failed to create "
785 "session description - ") +
786 error.message()));
787 operation_complete_callback_();
788 }
789
790 private:
791 bool was_called_ = false;
792 rtc::WeakPtr<SdpOfferAnswerHandler> sdp_handler_;
793 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface>
794 set_local_description_observer_;
795 std::function<void()> operation_complete_callback_;
796};

798// Wraps a CreateSessionDescriptionObserver and an OperationsChain operation
799// complete callback. When the observer is invoked, the wrapped observer is
800// invoked followed by invoking the completion callback.
801class CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper
802 : public CreateSessionDescriptionObserver {
803 public:
804 CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper(
805 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserver> observer,
806 std::function<void()> operation_complete_callback)
807 : observer_(std::move(observer)),
808 operation_complete_callback_(std::move(operation_complete_callback)) {
809 RTC_DCHECK(observer_);
810 }
811 ~CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper() override {
812#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
813 RTC_DCHECK(was_called_);
814#endif
815 }
816
817 void OnSuccess(SessionDescriptionInterface* desc) override {
818#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
819 RTC_DCHECK(!was_called_);
820 was_called_ = true;
821#endif // RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
822 // Completing the operation before invoking the observer allows the observer
823 // to execute SetLocalDescription() without delay.
824 operation_complete_callback_();
825 observer_->OnSuccess(desc);
826 }
827
828 void OnFailure(RTCError error) override {
829#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
830 RTC_DCHECK(!was_called_);
831 was_called_ = true;
832#endif // RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
833 operation_complete_callback_();
834 observer_->OnFailure(std::move(error));
835 }
836
837 private:
838#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
839 bool was_called_ = false;
840#endif // RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
841 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserver> observer_;
842 std::function<void()> operation_complete_callback_;
843};
844
845// Wrapper for SetSessionDescriptionObserver that invokes the success or failure
846// callback in a posted message handled by the peer connection. This introduces
847// a delay that prevents recursive API calls by the observer, but this also
848// means that the PeerConnection can be modified before the observer sees the
849// result of the operation. This is ill-advised for synchronizing states.
850//
851// Implements both the SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface and the
852// SetRemoteDescriptionObserverInterface.
853class SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter
854 : public SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface,
855 public SetRemoteDescriptionObserverInterface {
856 public:
857 SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter(
858 rtc::WeakPtr<SdpOfferAnswerHandler> handler,
859 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetSessionDescriptionObserver> inner_observer)
860 : handler_(std::move(handler)),
861 inner_observer_(std::move(inner_observer)) {}
862
863 // SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface implementation.
864 void OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(RTCError error) override {
865 OnSetDescriptionComplete(std::move(error));
866 }
867 // SetRemoteDescriptionObserverInterface implementation.
868 void OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(RTCError error) override {
869 OnSetDescriptionComplete(std::move(error));
870 }
871
872 private:
873 void OnSetDescriptionComplete(RTCError error) {
874 if (!handler_)
875 return;
876 if (error.ok()) {
877 handler_->pc_->message_handler()->PostSetSessionDescriptionSuccess(
878 inner_observer_);
879 } else {
880 handler_->pc_->message_handler()->PostSetSessionDescriptionFailure(
881 inner_observer_, std::move(error));
882 }
883 }
884
885 rtc::WeakPtr<SdpOfferAnswerHandler> handler_;
886 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetSessionDescriptionObserver> inner_observer_;
887};
888
889class SdpOfferAnswerHandler::LocalIceCredentialsToReplace {
890 public:
891 // Sets the ICE credentials that need restarting to the ICE credentials of
892 // the current and pending descriptions.
893 void SetIceCredentialsFromLocalDescriptions(
894 const SessionDescriptionInterface* current_local_description,
895 const SessionDescriptionInterface* pending_local_description) {
896 ice_credentials_.clear();
897 if (current_local_description) {
898 AppendIceCredentialsFromSessionDescription(*current_local_description);
899 }
900 if (pending_local_description) {
901 AppendIceCredentialsFromSessionDescription(*pending_local_description);
902 }
903 }
904
905 void ClearIceCredentials() { ice_credentials_.clear(); }
906
907 // Returns true if we have ICE credentials that need restarting.
908 bool HasIceCredentials() const { return !ice_credentials_.empty(); }
909
910 // Returns true if |local_description| shares no ICE credentials with the
911 // ICE credentials that need restarting.
912 bool SatisfiesIceRestart(
913 const SessionDescriptionInterface& local_description) const {
914 for (const auto& transport_info :
915 local_description.description()->transport_infos()) {
916 if (ice_credentials_.find(std::make_pair(
917 transport_info.description.ice_ufrag,
918 transport_info.description.ice_pwd)) != ice_credentials_.end()) {
919 return false;
920 }
921 }
922 return true;
923 }
924
925 private:
926 void AppendIceCredentialsFromSessionDescription(
927 const SessionDescriptionInterface& desc) {
928 for (const auto& transport_info : desc.description()->transport_infos()) {
929 ice_credentials_.insert(
930 std::make_pair(transport_info.description.ice_ufrag,
931 transport_info.description.ice_pwd));
932 }
933 }
934
935 std::set<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> ice_credentials_;
936};

966void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::Initialize(
967 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& configuration,
968 PeerConnectionDependencies& dependencies) {
969 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
970 video_options_.screencast_min_bitrate_kbps =
971 configuration.screencast_min_bitrate;
972 audio_options_.combined_audio_video_bwe =
973 configuration.combined_audio_video_bwe;
974
975 audio_options_.audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets =
976 configuration.audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets;
977
978 audio_options_.audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate =
979 configuration.audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate;
980
981 audio_options_.audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms =
982 configuration.audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms;
983
984 audio_options_.audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling =
985 configuration.audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling;
986
987 // Obtain a certificate from RTCConfiguration if any were provided (optional).
988 rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate> certificate;
989 if (!configuration.certificates.empty()) {
990 // TODO(hbos,torbjorng): Decide on certificate-selection strategy instead of
991 // just picking the first one. The decision should be made based on the DTLS
992 // handshake. The DTLS negotiations need to know about all certificates.
993 certificate = configuration.certificates[0];
994 }
995
996 webrtc_session_desc_factory_ =
997 std::make_unique<WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory>(
998 signaling_thread(), channel_manager(), this, pc_->session_id(),
999 pc_->dtls_enabled(), std::move(dependencies.cert_generator),
1000 certificate, &ssrc_generator_,
1001 [this](const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate) {
1002 transport_controller()->SetLocalCertificate(certificate);
1003 });
1004
1005 if (pc_->options()->disable_encryption) {
1006 webrtc_session_desc_factory_->SetSdesPolicy(cricket::SEC_DISABLED);
1007 }
1008
1009 webrtc_session_desc_factory_->set_enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions(
1010 pc_->GetCryptoOptions().srtp.enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions);
1011 webrtc_session_desc_factory_->set_is_unified_plan(IsUnifiedPlan());
1012
1013 if (dependencies.video_bitrate_allocator_factory) {
1014 video_bitrate_allocator_factory_ =
1015 std::move(dependencies.video_bitrate_allocator_factory);
1016 } else {
1017 video_bitrate_allocator_factory_ =
1018 CreateBuiltinVideoBitrateAllocatorFactory();
1019 }
1020}

1087
1088void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::CreateOffer(
1089 CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
1090 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& options) {
1091 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1092 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
1093 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
1094 // lambda will execute immediately.
1095 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
1096 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(),
1097 observer_refptr =
1098 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserver>(observer),
1099 options](std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) {
1100 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid.
1101 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
1102 observer_refptr->OnFailure(
1103 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
1104 "CreateOffer failed because the session was shut down"));
1105 operations_chain_callback();
1106 return;
1107 }
1108 // The operation completes asynchronously when the wrapper is invoked.
1109 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper>
1110 observer_wrapper(new rtc::RefCountedObject<
1111 CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper>(
1112 std::move(observer_refptr),
1113 std::move(operations_chain_callback)));
1114 this_weak_ptr->DoCreateOffer(options, observer_wrapper);
1115 });
1116}
1117
1118void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetLocalDescription(
1119 SetSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
1120 SessionDescriptionInterface* desc_ptr) {
1121 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1122 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
1123 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
1124 // lambda will execute immediately.
1125 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
1126 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(),
1127 observer_refptr =
1128 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetSessionDescriptionObserver>(observer),
1129 desc = std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface>(desc_ptr)](
1130 std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) mutable {
1131 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid.
1132 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
1133 // For consistency with SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter whose
1134 // posted messages doesn't get processed when the PC is destroyed, we
1135 // do not inform |observer_refptr| that the operation failed.
1136 operations_chain_callback();
1137 return;
1138 }
1139 // SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter takes care of making sure the
1140 // |observer_refptr| is invoked in a posted message.
1141 this_weak_ptr->DoSetLocalDescription(
1142 std::move(desc),
1143 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface>(
1144 new rtc::RefCountedObject<SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter>(
1145 this_weak_ptr, observer_refptr)));
1146 // For backwards-compatability reasons, we declare the operation as
1147 // completed here (rather than in a post), so that the operation chain
1148 // is not blocked by this operation when the observer is invoked. This
1149 // allows the observer to trigger subsequent offer/answer operations
1150 // synchronously if the operation chain is now empty.
1151 operations_chain_callback();
1152 });
1153}
1154
1155void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetLocalDescription(
1156 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc,
1157 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface> observer) {
1158 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1159 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
1160 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
1161 // lambda will execute immediately.
1162 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
1163 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), observer,
1164 desc = std::move(desc)](
1165 std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) mutable {
1166 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid.
1167 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
1168 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(RTCError(
1169 RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
1170 "SetLocalDescription failed because the session was shut down"));
1171 operations_chain_callback();
1172 return;
1173 }
1174 this_weak_ptr->DoSetLocalDescription(std::move(desc), observer);
1175 // DoSetLocalDescription() is implemented as a synchronous operation.
1176 // The |observer| will already have been informed that it completed, and
1177 // we can mark this operation as complete without any loose ends.
1178 operations_chain_callback();
1179 });
1180}
1181
1182void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetLocalDescription(
1183 SetSessionDescriptionObserver* observer) {
1184 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1185 SetLocalDescription(
1186 new rtc::RefCountedObject<SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter>(
1187 weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), observer));
1188}
1189
1190void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetLocalDescription(
1191 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface> observer) {
1192 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1193 // The |create_sdp_observer| handles performing DoSetLocalDescription() with
1194 // the resulting description as well as completing the operation.
1195 rtc::scoped_refptr<ImplicitCreateSessionDescriptionObserver>
1196 create_sdp_observer(
1197 new rtc::RefCountedObject<ImplicitCreateSessionDescriptionObserver>(
1198 weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), observer));
1199 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
1200 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
1201 // lambda will execute immediately.
1202 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
1203 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(),
1204 create_sdp_observer](std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) {
1205 // The |create_sdp_observer| is responsible for completing the
1206 // operation.
1207 create_sdp_observer->SetOperationCompleteCallback(
1208 std::move(operations_chain_callback));
1209 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid. This triggers the
1210 // same code path as if DoCreateOffer() or DoCreateAnswer() failed.
1211 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
1212 create_sdp_observer->OnFailure(RTCError(
1213 RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
1214 "SetLocalDescription failed because the session was shut down"));
1215 return;
1216 }
1217 switch (this_weak_ptr->signaling_state()) {
1218 case PeerConnectionInterface::kStable:
1219 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalOffer:
1220 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemotePrAnswer:
1221 // TODO(hbos): If [LastCreatedOffer] exists and still represents the
1222 // current state of the system, use that instead of creating another
1223 // offer.
1224 this_weak_ptr->DoCreateOffer(
1225 PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions(),
1226 create_sdp_observer);
1227 break;
1228 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalPrAnswer:
1229 case PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemoteOffer:
1230 // TODO(hbos): If [LastCreatedAnswer] exists and still represents
1231 // the current state of the system, use that instead of creating
1232 // another answer.
1233 this_weak_ptr->DoCreateAnswer(
1234 PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions(),
1235 create_sdp_observer);
1236 break;
1237 case PeerConnectionInterface::kClosed:
1238 create_sdp_observer->OnFailure(RTCError(
1239 RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
1240 "SetLocalDescription called when PeerConnection is closed."));
1241 break;
1242 }
1243 });
1244}
1245
1246RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ApplyLocalDescription(
1247 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc,
1248 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
1249 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
1250 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1251 RTC_DCHECK(desc);
1252
1253 // Update stats here so that we have the most recent stats for tracks and
1254 // streams that might be removed by updating the session description.
1255 pc_->stats()->UpdateStats(PeerConnectionInterface::kStatsOutputLevelStandard);
1256
1257 // Take a reference to the old local description since it's used below to
1258 // compare against the new local description. When setting the new local
1259 // description, grab ownership of the replaced session description in case it
1260 // is the same as |old_local_description|, to keep it alive for the duration
1261 // of the method.
1262 const SessionDescriptionInterface* old_local_description =
1263 local_description();
1264 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> replaced_local_description;
1265 SdpType type = desc->GetType();
1266 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
1267 replaced_local_description = pending_local_description_
1268 ? std::move(pending_local_description_)
1269 : std::move(current_local_description_);
1270 current_local_description_ = std::move(desc);
1271 pending_local_description_ = nullptr;
1272 current_remote_description_ = std::move(pending_remote_description_);
1273 } else {
1274 replaced_local_description = std::move(pending_local_description_);
1275 pending_local_description_ = std::move(desc);
1276 }
1277 // The session description to apply now must be accessed by
1278 // |local_description()|.
1279 RTC_DCHECK(local_description());
1280
1281 // Report statistics about any use of simulcast.
1282 ReportSimulcastApiVersion(kSimulcastVersionApplyLocalDescription,
1283 *local_description()->description());
1284
1285 if (!is_caller_) {
1286 if (remote_description()) {
1287 // Remote description was applied first, so this PC is the callee.
1288 is_caller_ = false;
1289 } else {
1290 // Local description is applied first, so this PC is the caller.
1291 is_caller_ = true;
1292 }
1293 }
1294
1295 RTCError error = PushdownTransportDescription(cricket::CS_LOCAL, type);
1296 if (!error.ok()) {
1297 return error;
1298 }
1299
1300 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1301 RTCError error = UpdateTransceiversAndDataChannels(
1302 cricket::CS_LOCAL, *local_description(), old_local_description,
1303 remote_description(), bundle_groups_by_mid);
1304 if (!error.ok()) {
1305 return error;
1306 }
1307 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverInterface>> remove_list;
1308 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> removed_streams;
1309 for (const auto& transceiver_ext : transceivers()->List()) {
1310 auto transceiver = transceiver_ext->internal();
1311 if (transceiver->stopped()) {
1312 continue;
1313 }
1314
1315 // 2.2.7.1.1.(6-9): Set sender and receiver's transport slots.
1316 // Note that code paths that don't set MID won't be able to use
1317 // information about DTLS transports.
1318 if (transceiver->mid()) {
1319 auto dtls_transport = LookupDtlsTransportByMid(
1320 pc_->network_thread(), transport_controller(), *transceiver->mid());
1321 transceiver->sender_internal()->set_transport(dtls_transport);
1322 transceiver->receiver_internal()->set_transport(dtls_transport);
1323 }
1324
1325 const ContentInfo* content =
1326 FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(transceiver, local_description());
1327 if (!content) {
1328 continue;
1329 }
1330 const MediaContentDescription* media_desc = content->media_description();
1331 // 2.2.7.1.6: If description is of type "answer" or "pranswer", then run
1332 // the following steps:
1333 if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
1334 // 2.2.7.1.6.1: If direction is "sendonly" or "inactive", and
1335 // transceiver's [[FiredDirection]] slot is either "sendrecv" or
1336 // "recvonly", process the removal of a remote track for the media
1337 // description, given transceiver, removeList, and muteTracks.
1338 if (!RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(media_desc->direction()) &&
1339 (transceiver->fired_direction() &&
1340 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(*transceiver->fired_direction()))) {
1341 ProcessRemovalOfRemoteTrack(transceiver_ext, &remove_list,
1342 &removed_streams);
1343 }
1344 // 2.2.7.1.6.2: Set transceiver's [[CurrentDirection]] and
1345 // [[FiredDirection]] slots to direction.
1346 transceiver->set_current_direction(media_desc->direction());
1347 transceiver->set_fired_direction(media_desc->direction());
1348 }
1349 }
1350 auto observer = pc_->Observer();
1351 for (const auto& transceiver : remove_list) {
1352 observer->OnRemoveTrack(transceiver->receiver());
1353 }
1354 for (const auto& stream : removed_streams) {
1355 observer->OnRemoveStream(stream);
1356 }
1357 } else {
1358 // Media channels will be created only when offer is set. These may use new
1359 // transports just created by PushdownTransportDescription.
1360 if (type == SdpType::kOffer) {
1361 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/4676) - Handle CreateChannel failure, as new local
1362 // description is applied. Restore back to old description.
1363 RTCError error = CreateChannels(*local_description()->description());
1364 if (!error.ok()) {
1365 return error;
1366 }
1367 }
1368 // Remove unused channels if MediaContentDescription is rejected.
1369 RemoveUnusedChannels(local_description()->description());
1370 }
1371
1372 error = UpdateSessionState(type, cricket::CS_LOCAL,
1373 local_description()->description(),
1374 bundle_groups_by_mid);
1375 if (!error.ok()) {
1376 return error;
1377 }
1378
1379 if (remote_description()) {
1380 // Now that we have a local description, we can push down remote candidates.
1381 UseCandidatesInSessionDescription(remote_description());
1382 }
1383
1384 pending_ice_restarts_.clear();
1385 if (session_error() != SessionError::kNone) {
1386 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, GetSessionErrorMsg());
1387 }
1388
1389 // If setting the description decided our SSL role, allocate any necessary
1390 // SCTP sids.
1391 rtc::SSLRole role;
1392 if (pc_->GetSctpSslRole(&role)) {
1393 data_channel_controller()->AllocateSctpSids(role);
1394 }
1395
1396 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1397 // We must use List and not ListInternal here because
1398 // transceivers()->StableState() is indexed by the non-internal refptr.
1399 for (const auto& transceiver_ext : transceivers()->List()) {
1400 auto transceiver = transceiver_ext->internal();
1401 if (transceiver->stopped()) {
1402 continue;
1403 }
1404 const ContentInfo* content =
1405 FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(transceiver, local_description());
1406 if (!content) {
1407 continue;
1408 }
1409 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->channel();
1410 if (content->rejected || !channel || channel->local_streams().empty()) {
1411 // 0 is a special value meaning "this sender has no associated send
1412 // stream". Need to call this so the sender won't attempt to configure
1413 // a no longer existing stream and run into DCHECKs in the lower
1414 // layers.
1415 transceiver->sender_internal()->SetSsrc(0);
1416 } else {
1417 // Get the StreamParams from the channel which could generate SSRCs.
1418 const std::vector<StreamParams>& streams = channel->local_streams();
1419 transceiver->sender_internal()->set_stream_ids(streams[0].stream_ids());
1420 auto encodings = transceiver->sender_internal()->init_send_encodings();
1421 transceiver->sender_internal()->SetSsrc(streams[0].first_ssrc());
1422 if (!encodings.empty()) {
1423 transceivers()
1424 ->StableState(transceiver_ext)
1425 ->SetInitSendEncodings(encodings);
1426 }
1427 }
1428 }
1429 } else {
1430 // Plan B semantics.
1431
1432 // Update state and SSRC of local MediaStreams and DataChannels based on the
1433 // local session description.
1434 const cricket::ContentInfo* audio_content =
1435 GetFirstAudioContent(local_description()->description());
1436 if (audio_content) {
1437 if (audio_content->rejected) {
1438 RemoveSenders(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO);
1439 } else {
1440 const cricket::AudioContentDescription* audio_desc =
1441 audio_content->media_description()->as_audio();
1442 UpdateLocalSenders(audio_desc->streams(), audio_desc->type());
1443 }
1444 }
1445
1446 const cricket::ContentInfo* video_content =
1447 GetFirstVideoContent(local_description()->description());
1448 if (video_content) {
1449 if (video_content->rejected) {
1450 RemoveSenders(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
1451 } else {
1452 const cricket::VideoContentDescription* video_desc =
1453 video_content->media_description()->as_video();
1454 UpdateLocalSenders(video_desc->streams(), video_desc->type());
1455 }
1456 }
1457 }
1458
1459 // This function does nothing with data content.
1460
1461 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer &&
1462 local_ice_credentials_to_replace_->SatisfiesIceRestart(
1463 *current_local_description_)) {
1464 local_ice_credentials_to_replace_->ClearIceCredentials();
1465 }
1466
1467 return RTCError::OK();
1468}
1469
1470void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetRemoteDescription(
1471 SetSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
1472 SessionDescriptionInterface* desc_ptr) {
1473 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1474 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
1475 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
1476 // lambda will execute immediately.
1477 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
1478 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(),
1479 observer_refptr =
1480 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetSessionDescriptionObserver>(observer),
1481 desc = std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface>(desc_ptr)](
1482 std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) mutable {
1483 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid.
1484 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
1485 // For consistency with SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter whose
1486 // posted messages doesn't get processed when the PC is destroyed, we
1487 // do not inform |observer_refptr| that the operation failed.
1488 operations_chain_callback();
1489 return;
1490 }
1491 // SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter takes care of making sure the
1492 // |observer_refptr| is invoked in a posted message.
1493 this_weak_ptr->DoSetRemoteDescription(
1494 std::move(desc),
1495 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetRemoteDescriptionObserverInterface>(
1496 new rtc::RefCountedObject<SetSessionDescriptionObserverAdapter>(
1497 this_weak_ptr, observer_refptr)));
1498 // For backwards-compatability reasons, we declare the operation as
1499 // completed here (rather than in a post), so that the operation chain
1500 // is not blocked by this operation when the observer is invoked. This
1501 // allows the observer to trigger subsequent offer/answer operations
1502 // synchronously if the operation chain is now empty.
1503 operations_chain_callback();
1504 });
1505}
1506
1507void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetRemoteDescription(
1508 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc,
1509 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetRemoteDescriptionObserverInterface> observer) {
1510 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1511 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
1512 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
1513 // lambda will execute immediately.
1514 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
1515 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), observer,
1516 desc = std::move(desc)](
1517 std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) mutable {
1518 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid.
1519 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
1520 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(RTCError(
1521 RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
1522 "SetRemoteDescription failed because the session was shut down"));
1523 operations_chain_callback();
1524 return;
1525 }
1526 this_weak_ptr->DoSetRemoteDescription(std::move(desc),
1527 std::move(observer));
1528 // DoSetRemoteDescription() is implemented as a synchronous operation.
1529 // The |observer| will already have been informed that it completed, and
1530 // we can mark this operation as complete without any loose ends.
1531 operations_chain_callback();
1532 });
1533}
1534
1535RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ApplyRemoteDescription(
1536 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc,
1537 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
1538 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
1539 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1540 RTC_DCHECK(desc);
1541
1542 // Update stats here so that we have the most recent stats for tracks and
1543 // streams that might be removed by updating the session description.
1544 pc_->stats()->UpdateStats(PeerConnectionInterface::kStatsOutputLevelStandard);
1545
1546 // Take a reference to the old remote description since it's used below to
1547 // compare against the new remote description. When setting the new remote
1548 // description, grab ownership of the replaced session description in case it
1549 // is the same as |old_remote_description|, to keep it alive for the duration
1550 // of the method.
1551 const SessionDescriptionInterface* old_remote_description =
1552 remote_description();
1553 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> replaced_remote_description;
1554 SdpType type = desc->GetType();
1555 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
1556 replaced_remote_description = pending_remote_description_
1557 ? std::move(pending_remote_description_)
1558 : std::move(current_remote_description_);
1559 current_remote_description_ = std::move(desc);
1560 pending_remote_description_ = nullptr;
1561 current_local_description_ = std::move(pending_local_description_);
1562 } else {
1563 replaced_remote_description = std::move(pending_remote_description_);
1564 pending_remote_description_ = std::move(desc);
1565 }
1566 // The session description to apply now must be accessed by
1567 // |remote_description()|.
1568 RTC_DCHECK(remote_description());
1569
1570 // Report statistics about any use of simulcast.
1571 ReportSimulcastApiVersion(kSimulcastVersionApplyRemoteDescription,
1572 *remote_description()->description());
1573
1574 RTCError error = PushdownTransportDescription(cricket::CS_REMOTE, type);
1575 if (!error.ok()) {
1576 return error;
1577 }
1578 // Transport and Media channels will be created only when offer is set.
1579 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1580 RTCError error = UpdateTransceiversAndDataChannels(
1581 cricket::CS_REMOTE, *remote_description(), local_description(),
1582 old_remote_description, bundle_groups_by_mid);
1583 if (!error.ok()) {
1584 return error;
1585 }
1586 } else {
1587 // Media channels will be created only when offer is set. These may use new
1588 // transports just created by PushdownTransportDescription.
1589 if (type == SdpType::kOffer) {
1590 // TODO(mallinath) - Handle CreateChannel failure, as new local
1591 // description is applied. Restore back to old description.
1592 RTCError error = CreateChannels(*remote_description()->description());
1593 if (!error.ok()) {
1594 return error;
1595 }
1596 }
1597 // Remove unused channels if MediaContentDescription is rejected.
1598 RemoveUnusedChannels(remote_description()->description());
1599 }
1600
1601 // NOTE: Candidates allocation will be initiated only when
1602 // SetLocalDescription is called.
1603 error = UpdateSessionState(type, cricket::CS_REMOTE,
1604 remote_description()->description(),
1605 bundle_groups_by_mid);
1606 if (!error.ok()) {
1607 return error;
1608 }
1609
1610 if (local_description() &&
1611 !UseCandidatesInSessionDescription(remote_description())) {
1612 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, kInvalidCandidates);
1613 }
1614
1615 if (old_remote_description) {
1616 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content :
1617 old_remote_description->description()->contents()) {
1618 // Check if this new SessionDescription contains new ICE ufrag and
1619 // password that indicates the remote peer requests an ICE restart.
1620 // TODO(deadbeef): When we start storing both the current and pending
1621 // remote description, this should reset pending_ice_restarts and compare
1622 // against the current description.
1623 if (CheckForRemoteIceRestart(old_remote_description, remote_description(),
1624 content.name)) {
1625 if (type == SdpType::kOffer) {
1626 pending_ice_restarts_.insert(content.name);
1627 }
1628 } else {
1629 // We retain all received candidates only if ICE is not restarted.
1630 // When ICE is restarted, all previous candidates belong to an old
1631 // generation and should not be kept.
1632 // TODO(deadbeef): This goes against the W3C spec which says the remote
1633 // description should only contain candidates from the last set remote
1634 // description plus any candidates added since then. We should remove
1635 // this once we're sure it won't break anything.
1636 WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::CopyCandidatesFromSessionDescription(
1637 old_remote_description, content.name, mutable_remote_description());
1638 }
1639 }
1640 }
1641
1642 if (session_error() != SessionError::kNone) {
1643 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, GetSessionErrorMsg());
1644 }
1645
1646 // Set the the ICE connection state to connecting since the connection may
1647 // become writable with peer reflexive candidates before any remote candidate
1648 // is signaled.
1649 // TODO(pthatcher): This is a short-term solution for crbug/446908. A real fix
1650 // is to have a new signal the indicates a change in checking state from the
1651 // transport and expose a new checking() member from transport that can be
1652 // read to determine the current checking state. The existing SignalConnecting
1653 // actually means "gathering candidates", so cannot be be used here.
1654 if (remote_description()->GetType() != SdpType::kOffer &&
1655 remote_description()->number_of_mediasections() > 0u &&
1656 pc_->ice_connection_state() ==
1657 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionNew) {
1658 pc_->SetIceConnectionState(PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionChecking);
1659 }
1660
1661 // If setting the description decided our SSL role, allocate any necessary
1662 // SCTP sids.
1663 rtc::SSLRole role;
1664 if (pc_->GetSctpSslRole(&role)) {
1665 data_channel_controller()->AllocateSctpSids(role);
1666 }
1667
1668 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1669 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverInterface>>
1670 now_receiving_transceivers;
1671 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverInterface>> remove_list;
1672 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> added_streams;
1673 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> removed_streams;
1674 for (const auto& transceiver_ext : transceivers()->List()) {
1675 const auto transceiver = transceiver_ext->internal();
1676 const ContentInfo* content =
1677 FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(transceiver, remote_description());
1678 if (!content) {
1679 continue;
1680 }
1681 const MediaContentDescription* media_desc = content->media_description();
1682 RtpTransceiverDirection local_direction =
1683 RtpTransceiverDirectionReversed(media_desc->direction());
1684 // Roughly the same as steps 2.2.8.6 of section 4.4.1.6 "Set the
1685 // RTCSessionDescription: Set the associated remote streams given
1686 // transceiver.[[Receiver]], msids, addList, and removeList".
1687 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#set-the-rtcsessiondescription
1688 if (RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(local_direction)) {
1689 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids;
1690 if (!media_desc->streams().empty()) {
1691 // The remote description has signaled the stream IDs.
1692 stream_ids = media_desc->streams()[0].stream_ids();
1693 }
1694 transceivers()
1695 ->StableState(transceiver_ext)
1696 ->SetRemoteStreamIdsIfUnset(transceiver->receiver()->stream_ids());
1697
1698 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Processing the MSIDs for MID=" << content->name
1699 << " (" << GetStreamIdsString(stream_ids) << ").";
1700 SetAssociatedRemoteStreams(transceiver->receiver_internal(), stream_ids,
1701 &added_streams, &removed_streams);
1702 // From the WebRTC specification, steps 2.2.8.5/6 of section 4.4.1.6
1703 // "Set the RTCSessionDescription: If direction is sendrecv or recvonly,
1704 // and transceiver's current direction is neither sendrecv nor recvonly,
1705 // process the addition of a remote track for the media description.
1706 if (!transceiver->fired_direction() ||
1707 !RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(*transceiver->fired_direction())) {
1708 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1709 << "Processing the addition of a remote track for MID="
1710 << content->name << ".";
1711 now_receiving_transceivers.push_back(transceiver);
1712 }
1713 }
1714 // 2.2.8.1.9: If direction is "sendonly" or "inactive", and transceiver's
1715 // [[FiredDirection]] slot is either "sendrecv" or "recvonly", process the
1716 // removal of a remote track for the media description, given transceiver,
1717 // removeList, and muteTracks.
1718 if (!RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(local_direction) &&
1719 (transceiver->fired_direction() &&
1720 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(*transceiver->fired_direction()))) {
1721 ProcessRemovalOfRemoteTrack(transceiver_ext, &remove_list,
1722 &removed_streams);
1723 }
1724 // 2.2.8.1.10: Set transceiver's [[FiredDirection]] slot to direction.
1725 transceiver->set_fired_direction(local_direction);
1726 // 2.2.8.1.11: If description is of type "answer" or "pranswer", then run
1727 // the following steps:
1728 if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
1729 // 2.2.8.1.11.1: Set transceiver's [[CurrentDirection]] slot to
1730 // direction.
1731 transceiver->set_current_direction(local_direction);
1732 // 2.2.8.1.11.[3-6]: Set the transport internal slots.
1733 if (transceiver->mid()) {
1734 auto dtls_transport = LookupDtlsTransportByMid(pc_->network_thread(),
1735 transport_controller(),
1736 *transceiver->mid());
1737 transceiver->sender_internal()->set_transport(dtls_transport);
1738 transceiver->receiver_internal()->set_transport(dtls_transport);
1739 }
1740 }
1741 // 2.2.8.1.12: If the media description is rejected, and transceiver is
1742 // not already stopped, stop the RTCRtpTransceiver transceiver.
1743 if (content->rejected && !transceiver->stopped()) {
1744 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Stopping transceiver for MID=" << content->name
1745 << " since the media section was rejected.";
1746 transceiver->StopTransceiverProcedure();
1747 }
1748 if (!content->rejected &&
1749 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(local_direction)) {
1750 if (!media_desc->streams().empty() &&
1751 media_desc->streams()[0].has_ssrcs()) {
1752 uint32_t ssrc = media_desc->streams()[0].first_ssrc();
1753 transceiver->receiver_internal()->SetupMediaChannel(ssrc);
1754 } else {
1755 transceiver->receiver_internal()->SetupUnsignaledMediaChannel();
1756 }
1757 }
1758 }
1759 // Once all processing has finished, fire off callbacks.
1760 auto observer = pc_->Observer();
1761 for (const auto& transceiver : now_receiving_transceivers) {
1762 pc_->stats()->AddTrack(transceiver->receiver()->track());
1763#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
1764 // FIXME: We should probably move out of OnTrack and get the list of transceivers in description applied callback.
1765 for (const auto& transceiver_ext : transceivers()->List()) {
1766 if (transceiver.get() == transceiver_ext->internal())
1767 observer->OnTrack(transceiver_ext);
1768 }
1769#else
1770 observer->OnTrack(transceiver);
1771#endif
1772 observer->OnAddTrack(transceiver->receiver(),
1773 transceiver->receiver()->streams());
1774 }
1775 for (const auto& stream : added_streams) {
1776 observer->OnAddStream(stream);
1777 }
1778 for (const auto& transceiver : remove_list) {
1779 observer->OnRemoveTrack(transceiver->receiver());
1780 }
1781 for (const auto& stream : removed_streams) {
1782 observer->OnRemoveStream(stream);
1783 }
1784 }
1785
1786 const cricket::ContentInfo* audio_content =
1787 GetFirstAudioContent(remote_description()->description());
1788 const cricket::ContentInfo* video_content =
1789 GetFirstVideoContent(remote_description()->description());
1790 const cricket::AudioContentDescription* audio_desc =
1791 GetFirstAudioContentDescription(remote_description()->description());
1792 const cricket::VideoContentDescription* video_desc =
1793 GetFirstVideoContentDescription(remote_description()->description());
1794
1795 // Check if the descriptions include streams, just in case the peer supports
1796 // MSID, but doesn't indicate so with "a=msid-semantic".
1797 if (remote_description()->description()->msid_supported() ||
1798 (audio_desc && !audio_desc->streams().empty()) ||
1799 (video_desc && !video_desc->streams().empty())) {
1800 remote_peer_supports_msid_ = true;
1801 }
1802
1803 // We wait to signal new streams until we finish processing the description,
1804 // since only at that point will new streams have all their tracks.
1805 rtc::scoped_refptr<StreamCollection> new_streams(StreamCollection::Create());
1806
1807 if (!IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1808 // TODO(steveanton): When removing RTP senders/receivers in response to a
1809 // rejected media section, there is some cleanup logic that expects the
1810 // voice/ video channel to still be set. But in this method the voice/video
1811 // channel would have been destroyed by the SetRemoteDescription caller
1812 // above so the cleanup that relies on them fails to run. The RemoveSenders
1813 // calls should be moved to right before the DestroyChannel calls to fix
1814 // this.
1815
1816 // Find all audio rtp streams and create corresponding remote AudioTracks
1817 // and MediaStreams.
1818 if (audio_content) {
1819 if (audio_content->rejected) {
1820 RemoveSenders(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO);
1821 } else {
1822 bool default_audio_track_needed =
1823 !remote_peer_supports_msid_ &&
1824 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(audio_desc->direction());
1825 UpdateRemoteSendersList(GetActiveStreams(audio_desc),
1826 default_audio_track_needed, audio_desc->type(),
1827 new_streams);
1828 }
1829 }
1830
1831 // Find all video rtp streams and create corresponding remote VideoTracks
1832 // and MediaStreams.
1833 if (video_content) {
1834 if (video_content->rejected) {
1835 RemoveSenders(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
1836 } else {
1837 bool default_video_track_needed =
1838 !remote_peer_supports_msid_ &&
1839 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(video_desc->direction());
1840 UpdateRemoteSendersList(GetActiveStreams(video_desc),
1841 default_video_track_needed, video_desc->type(),
1842 new_streams);
1843 }
1844 }
1845
1846 // Iterate new_streams and notify the observer about new MediaStreams.
1847 auto observer = pc_->Observer();
1848 for (size_t i = 0; i < new_streams->count(); ++i) {
1849 MediaStreamInterface* new_stream = new_streams->at(i);
1850 pc_->stats()->AddStream(new_stream);
1851 observer->OnAddStream(
1852 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>(new_stream));
1853 }
1854
1855 UpdateEndedRemoteMediaStreams();
1856 }
1857
1858 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer &&
1859 local_ice_credentials_to_replace_->SatisfiesIceRestart(
1860 *current_local_description_)) {
1861 local_ice_credentials_to_replace_->ClearIceCredentials();
1862 }
1863
1864 return RTCError::OK();
1865}
1866
1867void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoSetLocalDescription(
1868 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc,
1869 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetLocalDescriptionObserverInterface> observer) {
1870 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1871 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoSetLocalDescription");
1872
1873 if (!observer) {
1874 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetLocalDescription - observer is NULL.";
1875 return;
1876 }
1877
1878 if (!desc) {
1879 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(
1880 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, "SessionDescription is NULL."));
1881 return;
1882 }
1883
1884 // If a session error has occurred the PeerConnection is in a possibly
1885 // inconsistent state so fail right away.
1886 if (session_error() != SessionError::kNone) {
1887 std::string error_message = GetSessionErrorMsg();
1888 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetLocalDescription: " << error_message;
1889 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(
1890 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, std::move(error_message)));
1891 return;
1892 }
1893
1894 // For SLD we support only explicit rollback.
1895 if (desc->GetType() == SdpType::kRollback) {
1896 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1897 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(Rollback(desc->GetType()));
1898 } else {
1899 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(
1900 RTCError(RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION,
1901 "Rollback not supported in Plan B"));
1902 }
1903 return;
1904 }
1905
1906 std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*> bundle_groups_by_mid =
1907 GetBundleGroupsByMid(desc->description());
1908 RTCError error = ValidateSessionDescription(desc.get(), cricket::CS_LOCAL,
1909 bundle_groups_by_mid);
1910 if (!error.ok()) {
1911 std::string error_message = GetSetDescriptionErrorMessage(
1912 cricket::CS_LOCAL, desc->GetType(), error);
1913 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error_message;
1914 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(
1915 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, std::move(error_message)));
1916 return;
1917 }
1918
1919 // Grab the description type before moving ownership to ApplyLocalDescription,
1920 // which may destroy it before returning.
1921 const SdpType type = desc->GetType();
1922
1923 error = ApplyLocalDescription(std::move(desc), bundle_groups_by_mid);
1924 // |desc| may be destroyed at this point.
1925
1926 if (!error.ok()) {
1927 // If ApplyLocalDescription fails, the PeerConnection could be in an
1928 // inconsistent state, so act conservatively here and set the session error
1929 // so that future calls to SetLocalDescription/SetRemoteDescription fail.
1930 SetSessionError(SessionError::kContent, error.message());
1931 std::string error_message =
1932 GetSetDescriptionErrorMessage(cricket::CS_LOCAL, type, error);
1933 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error_message;
1934 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(
1935 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, std::move(error_message)));
1936 return;
1937 }
1938 RTC_DCHECK(local_description());
1939
1940 if (local_description()->GetType() == SdpType::kAnswer) {
1941 RemoveStoppedTransceivers();
1942
1943 // TODO(deadbeef): We already had to hop to the network thread for
1944 // MaybeStartGathering...
1945 pc_->network_thread()->Invoke<void>(
1946 RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] { port_allocator()->DiscardCandidatePool(); });
1947 // Make UMA notes about what was agreed to.
1948 ReportNegotiatedSdpSemantics(*local_description());
1949 }
1950
1951 observer->OnSetLocalDescriptionComplete(RTCError::OK());
1952 pc_->NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::SET_LOCAL_DESCRIPTION_SUCCEEDED);
1953
1954 // Check if negotiation is needed. We must do this after informing the
1955 // observer that SetLocalDescription() has completed to ensure negotiation is
1956 // not needed prior to the promise resolving.
1957 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
1958 bool was_negotiation_needed = is_negotiation_needed_;
1959 UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
1960 if (signaling_state() == PeerConnectionInterface::kStable &&
1961 was_negotiation_needed && is_negotiation_needed_) {
1962 // Legacy version.
1963 pc_->Observer()->OnRenegotiationNeeded();
1964 // Spec-compliant version; the event may get invalidated before firing.
1965 GenerateNegotiationNeededEvent();
1966 }
1967 }
1968
1969 // MaybeStartGathering needs to be called after informing the observer so that
1970 // we don't signal any candidates before signaling that SetLocalDescription
1971 // completed.
1972 transport_controller()->MaybeStartGathering();
1973}

1975void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoCreateOffer(

1981 if (!observer) {
1982 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "CreateOffer - observer is NULL.";
1983 return;
1984 }
1985
1986 if (pc_->IsClosed()) {
1987 std::string error = "CreateOffer called when PeerConnection is closed.";
1988 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;

2029void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::CreateAnswer(
2030 CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
2031 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& options) {
2032 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2033 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
2034 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
2035 // lambda will execute immediately.
2036 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
2037 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(),
2038 observer_refptr =
2039 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserver>(observer),
2040 options](std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) {
2041 // Abort early if |this_weak_ptr| is no longer valid.
2042 if (!this_weak_ptr) {
2043 observer_refptr->OnFailure(RTCError(
2044 RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
2045 "CreateAnswer failed because the session was shut down"));
2046 operations_chain_callback();
2047 return;
2048 }
2049 // The operation completes asynchronously when the wrapper is invoked.
2050 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper>
2051 observer_wrapper(new rtc::RefCountedObject<
2052 CreateSessionDescriptionObserverOperationWrapper>(
2053 std::move(observer_refptr),
2054 std::move(operations_chain_callback)));
2055 this_weak_ptr->DoCreateAnswer(options, observer_wrapper);
2056 });
2057}

2059void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoCreateAnswer(
2060 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& options,
2061 rtc::scoped_refptr<CreateSessionDescriptionObserver> observer) {
2062 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2063 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoCreateAnswer");
2064 if (!observer) {
2065 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "CreateAnswer - observer is NULL.";
2066 return;
2067 }
2068
2069 // If a session error has occurred the PeerConnection is in a possibly
2070 // inconsistent state so fail right away.
2071 if (session_error() != SessionError::kNone) {
2072 std::string error_message = GetSessionErrorMsg();
2073 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "CreateAnswer: " << error_message;
2074 pc_->message_handler()->PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailure(
2075 observer,
2076 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, std::move(error_message)));
2077 return;
2078 }
2079
2080 if (!(signaling_state_ == PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemoteOffer ||
2081 signaling_state_ == PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalPrAnswer)) {

2092 RTC_DCHECK(remote_description());

2096 PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions::kUndefined) {
2097 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "CreateAnswer: offer_to_receive_audio is not "
2098 "supported with Unified Plan semantics. Use the "
2099 "RtpTransceiver API instead.";
2100 }
2101 if (options.offer_to_receive_video !=
2102 PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions::kUndefined) {

2104 "supported with Unified Plan semantics. Use the "
2105 "RtpTransceiver API instead.";
2106 }
2107 }

2109 cricket::MediaSessionOptions session_options;
2110 GetOptionsForAnswer(options, &session_options);
2111 webrtc_session_desc_factory_->CreateAnswer(observer, session_options);

2114void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoSetRemoteDescription(
2115 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> desc,
2116 rtc::scoped_refptr<SetRemoteDescriptionObserverInterface> observer) {
2117 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2118 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DoSetRemoteDescription");
2119
2120 if (!observer) {
2121 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetRemoteDescription - observer is NULL.";
2122 return;
2123 }
2124
2125 if (!desc) {
2126 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(RTCError(
2127 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, "SessionDescription is NULL."));
2128 return;
2129 }
2130
2131 // If a session error has occurred the PeerConnection is in a possibly
2132 // inconsistent state so fail right away.
2133 if (session_error() != SessionError::kNone) {
2134 std::string error_message = GetSessionErrorMsg();
2135 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetRemoteDescription: " << error_message;
2136 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(
2137 RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, std::move(error_message)));
2138 return;
2139 }
2140 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
2141 if (pc_->configuration()->enable_implicit_rollback) {
2142 if (desc->GetType() == SdpType::kOffer &&
2143 signaling_state() == PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalOffer) {
2144 Rollback(desc->GetType());
2145 }
2146 }
2147 // Explicit rollback.
2148 if (desc->GetType() == SdpType::kRollback) {
2149 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(Rollback(desc->GetType()));
2150 return;
2151 }
2152 } else if (desc->GetType() == SdpType::kRollback) {
2153 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(
2154 RTCError(RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION,
2155 "Rollback not supported in Plan B"));
2156 return;
2157 }
2158 if (desc->GetType() == SdpType::kOffer ||
2159 desc->GetType() == SdpType::kAnswer) {
2160 // Report to UMA the format of the received offer or answer.
2161 pc_->ReportSdpFormatReceived(*desc);
2162 pc_->ReportSdpBundleUsage(*desc);
2163 }
2164
2165 // Handle remote descriptions missing a=mid lines for interop with legacy end
2166 // points.
2167 FillInMissingRemoteMids(desc->description());
2168
2169 std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*> bundle_groups_by_mid =
2170 GetBundleGroupsByMid(desc->description());
2171 RTCError error = ValidateSessionDescription(desc.get(), cricket::CS_REMOTE,
2172 bundle_groups_by_mid);
2173 if (!error.ok()) {
2174 std::string error_message = GetSetDescriptionErrorMessage(
2175 cricket::CS_REMOTE, desc->GetType(), error);
2176 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error_message;
2177 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(
2178 RTCError(error.type(), std::move(error_message)));
2179 return;
2180 }

2182 // Grab the description type before moving ownership to
2183 // ApplyRemoteDescription, which may destroy it before returning.
2184 const SdpType type = desc->GetType();

2186 error = ApplyRemoteDescription(std::move(desc), bundle_groups_by_mid);
2187 // |desc| may be destroyed at this point.
2188
2189 if (!error.ok()) {
2190 // If ApplyRemoteDescription fails, the PeerConnection could be in an
2191 // inconsistent state, so act conservatively here and set the session error
2192 // so that future calls to SetLocalDescription/SetRemoteDescription fail.
2193 SetSessionError(SessionError::kContent, error.message());
2194 std::string error_message =
2195 GetSetDescriptionErrorMessage(cricket::CS_REMOTE, type, error);
2196 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error_message;
2197 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(
2198 RTCError(error.type(), std::move(error_message)));
2199 return;
2200 }
2201 RTC_DCHECK(remote_description());
2202
2203 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
2204 RemoveStoppedTransceivers();
2205 // TODO(deadbeef): We already had to hop to the network thread for
2206 // MaybeStartGathering...
2207 pc_->network_thread()->Invoke<void>(
2208 RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] { port_allocator()->DiscardCandidatePool(); });
2209 // Make UMA notes about what was agreed to.
2210 ReportNegotiatedSdpSemantics(*remote_description());
2211 }
2212
2213 observer->OnSetRemoteDescriptionComplete(RTCError::OK());
2214 pc_->NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::SET_REMOTE_DESCRIPTION_SUCCEEDED);
2215
2216 // Check if negotiation is needed. We must do this after informing the
2217 // observer that SetRemoteDescription() has completed to ensure negotiation is
2218 // not needed prior to the promise resolving.
2219 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
2220 bool was_negotiation_needed = is_negotiation_needed_;
2221 UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
2222 if (signaling_state() == PeerConnectionInterface::kStable &&
2223 was_negotiation_needed && is_negotiation_needed_) {
2224 // Legacy version.
2225 pc_->Observer()->OnRenegotiationNeeded();
2226 // Spec-compliant version; the event may get invalidated before firing.
2227 GenerateNegotiationNeededEvent();

2231
2232void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::SetAssociatedRemoteStreams(
2233 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal> receiver,
2234 const std::vector<std::string>& stream_ids,
2235 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>* added_streams,
2236 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>* removed_streams) {
2237 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2238 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> media_streams;
2239 for (const std::string& stream_id : stream_ids) {
2240 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface> stream =
2241 remote_streams_->find(stream_id);
2242 if (!stream) {
2243 stream = MediaStreamProxy::Create(rtc::Thread::Current(),
2244 MediaStream::Create(stream_id));
2245 remote_streams_->AddStream(stream);
2246 added_streams->push_back(stream);
2247 }
2248 media_streams.push_back(stream);
2249 }
2250 // Special case: "a=msid" missing, use random stream ID.
2251 if (media_streams.empty() &&
2252 !(remote_description()->description()->msid_signaling() &
2253 cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection)) {
2254 if (!missing_msid_default_stream_) {
2255 missing_msid_default_stream_ = MediaStreamProxy::Create(
2256 rtc::Thread::Current(), MediaStream::Create(rtc::CreateRandomUuid()));
2257 added_streams->push_back(missing_msid_default_stream_);
2258 }
2259 media_streams.push_back(missing_msid_default_stream_);
2260 }
2261 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> previous_streams =
2262 receiver->streams();
2263 // SetStreams() will add/remove the receiver's track to/from the streams. This
2264 // differs from the spec - the spec uses an "addList" and "removeList" to
2265 // update the stream-track relationships in a later step. We do this earlier,
2266 // changing the order of things, but the end-result is the same.
2267 // TODO(hbos): When we remove remote_streams(), use set_stream_ids()
2268 // instead. https://crbug.com/webrtc/9480
2269 receiver->SetStreams(media_streams);
2270 RemoveRemoteStreamsIfEmpty(previous_streams, removed_streams);
2271}
