2273bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AddIceCandidate(
2274 const IceCandidateInterface* ice_candidate) {
2275 const AddIceCandidateResult result = AddIceCandidateInternal(ice_candidate);
2276 NoteAddIceCandidateResult(result);
2277 // If the return value is kAddIceCandidateFailNotReady, the candidate has been
2278 // added, although not 'ready', but that's a success.
2279 return result == kAddIceCandidateSuccess ||
2280 result == kAddIceCandidateFailNotReady;
2281}
2282
2283AddIceCandidateResult SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AddIceCandidateInternal(
2284 const IceCandidateInterface* ice_candidate) {
2285 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2286 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AddIceCandidate");
2287 if (pc_->IsClosed()) {
2288 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "AddIceCandidate: PeerConnection is closed.";
2289 return kAddIceCandidateFailClosed;
2290 }
2291
2292 if (!remote_description()) {
2293 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "AddIceCandidate: ICE candidates can't be added "
2294 "without any remote session description.";
2295 return kAddIceCandidateFailNoRemoteDescription;
2296 }
2297
2298 if (!ice_candidate) {
2299 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "AddIceCandidate: Candidate is null.";
2300 return kAddIceCandidateFailNullCandidate;
2301 }
2302
2303 bool valid = false;
2304 bool ready = ReadyToUseRemoteCandidate(ice_candidate, nullptr, &valid);
2305 if (!valid) {
2306 return kAddIceCandidateFailNotValid;
2307 }
2308
2309 // Add this candidate to the remote session description.
2310 if (!mutable_remote_description()->AddCandidate(ice_candidate)) {
2311 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "AddIceCandidate: Candidate cannot be used.";
2312 return kAddIceCandidateFailInAddition;
2313 }
2314
2315 if (!ready) {
2316 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AddIceCandidate: Not ready to use candidate.";
2317 return kAddIceCandidateFailNotReady;
2318 }
2319
2320 if (!UseCandidate(ice_candidate)) {
2321 return kAddIceCandidateFailNotUsable;
2322 }
2323
2324 pc_->NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::ADD_ICE_CANDIDATE_SUCCEEDED);
2325
2326 return kAddIceCandidateSuccess;
2327}
2328
2329void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AddIceCandidate(
2330 std::unique_ptr<IceCandidateInterface> candidate,
2331 std::function<void(RTCError)> callback) {
2332 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2333 // Chain this operation. If asynchronous operations are pending on the chain,
2334 // this operation will be queued to be invoked, otherwise the contents of the
2335 // lambda will execute immediately.
2336 operations_chain_->ChainOperation(
2337 [this_weak_ptr = weak_ptr_factory_.GetWeakPtr(),
2338 candidate = std::move(candidate), callback = std::move(callback)](
2339 std::function<void()> operations_chain_callback) {
2340 auto result =
2341 this_weak_ptr
2342 ? this_weak_ptr->AddIceCandidateInternal(candidate.get())
2343 : kAddIceCandidateFailClosed;
2344 NoteAddIceCandidateResult(result);
2345 operations_chain_callback();
2346 if (result == kAddIceCandidateFailClosed) {
2347 callback(RTCError(
2348 RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
2349 "AddIceCandidate failed because the session was shut down"));
2350 } else if (result != kAddIceCandidateSuccess &&
2351 result != kAddIceCandidateFailNotReady) {
2352 // Fail with an error type and message consistent with Chromium.
2353 // TODO(hbos): Fail with error types according to spec.
2354 callback(RTCError(RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION,
2355 "Error processing ICE candidate"));
2356 } else {
2357 callback(RTCError::OK());
2358 }
2359 });
2360}
2361
2362bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::RemoveIceCandidates(
2363 const std::vector<cricket::Candidate>& candidates) {
2364 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "SdpOfferAnswerHandler::RemoveIceCandidates");
2365 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2366 if (pc_->IsClosed()) {
2367 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "RemoveIceCandidates: PeerConnection is closed.";
2368 return false;
2369 }
2370
2371 if (!remote_description()) {
2372 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "RemoveIceCandidates: ICE candidates can't be removed "
2373 "without any remote session description.";
2374 return false;
2375 }
2376
2377 if (candidates.empty()) {
2378 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "RemoveIceCandidates: candidates are empty.";
2379 return false;
2380 }
2381
2382 size_t number_removed =
2383 mutable_remote_description()->RemoveCandidates(candidates);
2384 if (number_removed != candidates.size()) {
2385 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
2386 << "RemoveIceCandidates: Failed to remove candidates. Requested "
2387 << candidates.size() << " but only " << number_removed
2388 << " are removed.";
2389 }
2390
2391 // Remove the candidates from the transport controller.
2392 RTCError error = transport_controller()->RemoveRemoteCandidates(candidates);
2393 if (!error.ok()) {
2394 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
2395 << "RemoveIceCandidates: Error when removing remote candidates: "
2396 << error.message();
2397 }
2398 return true;
2399}

2461void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ChangeSignalingState(
2462 PeerConnectionInterface::SignalingState signaling_state) {
2463 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2464 if (signaling_state_ == signaling_state) {
2465 return;
2466 }
2467 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Session: " << pc_->session_id() << " Old state: "
2468 << GetSignalingStateString(signaling_state_)
2469 << " New state: "
2470 << GetSignalingStateString(signaling_state);
2471 signaling_state_ = signaling_state;
2472 pc_->Observer()->OnSignalingChange(signaling_state_);
2473}
2474
2475RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UpdateSessionState(
2476 SdpType type,
2477 cricket::ContentSource source,
2478 const cricket::SessionDescription* description,
2479 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
2480 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
2481 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2482
2483 // If there's already a pending error then no state transition should happen.
2484 // But all call-sites should be verifying this before calling us!
2485 RTC_DCHECK(session_error() == SessionError::kNone);
2486
2487 // If this is answer-ish we're ready to let media flow.
2488 if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
2489 EnableSending();
2490 }
2491
2492 // Update the signaling state according to the specified state machine (see
2493 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#rtcsignalingstate-enum).
2494 if (type == SdpType::kOffer) {
2495 ChangeSignalingState(source == cricket::CS_LOCAL
2496 ? PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalOffer
2497 : PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemoteOffer);
2498 } else if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer) {
2499 ChangeSignalingState(source == cricket::CS_LOCAL
2500 ? PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalPrAnswer
2501 : PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemotePrAnswer);
2502 } else {
2503 RTC_DCHECK(type == SdpType::kAnswer);
2504 ChangeSignalingState(PeerConnectionInterface::kStable);
2505 transceivers()->DiscardStableStates();
2506 }
2507
2508 // Update internal objects according to the session description's media
2509 // descriptions.
2510 return PushdownMediaDescription(type, source, bundle_groups_by_mid);
2511}
2512
2513bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ShouldFireNegotiationNeededEvent(
2514 uint32_t event_id) {
2515 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2516 // Plan B? Always fire to conform with useless legacy behavior.
2517 if (!IsUnifiedPlan()) {
2518 return true;
2519 }
2520 // The event ID has been invalidated. Either negotiation is no longer needed
2521 // or a newer negotiation needed event has been generated.
2522 if (event_id != negotiation_needed_event_id_) {
2523 return false;
2524 }
2525 // The chain is no longer empty, update negotiation needed when it becomes
2526 // empty. This should generate a newer negotiation needed event, making this
2527 // one obsolete.
2528 if (!operations_chain_->IsEmpty()) {
2529 // Since we just suppressed an event that would have been fired, if
2530 // negotiation is still needed by the time the chain becomes empty again, we
2531 // must make sure to generate another event if negotiation is needed then.
2532 // This happens when |is_negotiation_needed_| goes from false to true, so we
2533 // set it to false until UpdateNegotiationNeeded() is called.
2534 is_negotiation_needed_ = false;
2535 update_negotiation_needed_on_empty_chain_ = true;
2536 return false;
2537 }
2538 // We must not fire if the signaling state is no longer "stable". If
2539 // negotiation is still needed when we return to "stable", a new negotiation
2540 // needed event will be generated, so this one can safely be suppressed.
2541 if (signaling_state_ != PeerConnectionInterface::kStable) {
2542 return false;
2543 }
2544 // All checks have passed - please fire "negotiationneeded" now!
2545 return true;
2546}

2566bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AddStream(MediaStreamInterface* local_stream) {
2567 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2568 RTC_CHECK(!IsUnifiedPlan()) << "AddStream is not available with Unified Plan "
2569 "SdpSemantics. Please use AddTrack instead.";
2570 if (pc_->IsClosed()) {
2571 return false;
2572 }
2573 if (!CanAddLocalMediaStream(local_streams_, local_stream)) {
2574 return false;
2575 }
2576
2577 local_streams_->AddStream(local_stream);
2578 MediaStreamObserver* observer = new MediaStreamObserver(local_stream);
2579 observer->SignalAudioTrackAdded.connect(
2580 this, &SdpOfferAnswerHandler::OnAudioTrackAdded);
2581 observer->SignalAudioTrackRemoved.connect(
2582 this, &SdpOfferAnswerHandler::OnAudioTrackRemoved);
2583 observer->SignalVideoTrackAdded.connect(
2584 this, &SdpOfferAnswerHandler::OnVideoTrackAdded);
2585 observer->SignalVideoTrackRemoved.connect(
2586 this, &SdpOfferAnswerHandler::OnVideoTrackRemoved);
2587 stream_observers_.push_back(std::unique_ptr<MediaStreamObserver>(observer));
2588
2589 for (const auto& track : local_stream->GetAudioTracks()) {
2590 rtp_manager()->AddAudioTrack(track.get(), local_stream);
2591 }
2592 for (const auto& track : local_stream->GetVideoTracks()) {
2593 rtp_manager()->AddVideoTrack(track.get(), local_stream);
2594 }
2595
2596 pc_->stats()->AddStream(local_stream);
2597 UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
2598 return true;
2599}

2602 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());

2604 "Plan SdpSemantics. Please use RemoveTrack "

2666RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::Rollback(SdpType desc_type) {
2667 auto state = signaling_state();
2668 if (state != PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveLocalOffer &&
2669 state != PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemoteOffer) {
2670 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
2671 "Called in wrong signalingState: " +
2672 GetSignalingStateString(signaling_state()));
2673 }
2674 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2675 RTC_DCHECK(IsUnifiedPlan());
2676 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> all_added_streams;
2677 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> all_removed_streams;
2678 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInterface>> removed_receivers;
2679
2680 for (auto&& transceivers_stable_state_pair : transceivers()->StableStates()) {
2681 auto transceiver = transceivers_stable_state_pair.first;
2682 auto state = transceivers_stable_state_pair.second;
2683
2684 if (state.remote_stream_ids()) {
2685 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> added_streams;
2686 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> removed_streams;
2687 SetAssociatedRemoteStreams(transceiver->internal()->receiver_internal(),
2688 state.remote_stream_ids().value(),
2689 &added_streams, &removed_streams);
2690 all_added_streams.insert(all_added_streams.end(), added_streams.begin(),
2691 added_streams.end());
2692 all_removed_streams.insert(all_removed_streams.end(),
2693 removed_streams.begin(),
2694 removed_streams.end());
2695 if (!state.has_m_section() && !state.newly_created()) {
2696 continue;
2697 }
2698 }
2699
2700 RTC_DCHECK(transceiver->internal()->mid().has_value());
2701 DestroyTransceiverChannel(transceiver);
2702
2703 if (signaling_state() == PeerConnectionInterface::kHaveRemoteOffer &&
2704 transceiver->receiver()) {
2705 removed_receivers.push_back(transceiver->receiver());
2706 }
2707 if (state.newly_created()) {
2708 if (transceiver->internal()->reused_for_addtrack()) {
2709 transceiver->internal()->set_created_by_addtrack(true);
2710 } else {
2711 transceivers()->Remove(transceiver);
2712 }
2713 }
2714 if (state.init_send_encodings()) {
2715 transceiver->internal()->sender_internal()->set_init_send_encodings(
2716 state.init_send_encodings().value());
2717 }
2718 transceiver->internal()->sender_internal()->set_transport(nullptr);
2719 transceiver->internal()->receiver_internal()->set_transport(nullptr);
2720 transceiver->internal()->set_mid(state.mid());
2721 transceiver->internal()->set_mline_index(state.mline_index());
2722 }
2723 transport_controller()->RollbackTransports();
2724 transceivers()->DiscardStableStates();
2725 pending_local_description_.reset();
2726 pending_remote_description_.reset();
2727 ChangeSignalingState(PeerConnectionInterface::kStable);
2728
2729 // Once all processing has finished, fire off callbacks.
2730 for (const auto& receiver : removed_receivers) {
2731 pc_->Observer()->OnRemoveTrack(receiver);
2732 }
2733 for (const auto& stream : all_added_streams) {
2734 pc_->Observer()->OnAddStream(stream);
2735 }
2736 for (const auto& stream : all_removed_streams) {
2737 pc_->Observer()->OnRemoveStream(stream);
2738 }
2739
2740 // The assumption is that in case of implicit rollback UpdateNegotiationNeeded
2741 // gets called in SetRemoteDescription.
2742 if (desc_type == SdpType::kRollback) {
2743 UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
2744 if (is_negotiation_needed_) {
2745 // Legacy version.
2746 pc_->Observer()->OnRenegotiationNeeded();
2747 // Spec-compliant version; the event may get invalidated before firing.
2748 GenerateNegotiationNeededEvent();
2749 }
2750 }
2751 return RTCError::OK();
2752}

2756}

2758void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::OnOperationsChainEmpty() {
2759 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2760 if (pc_->IsClosed() || !update_negotiation_needed_on_empty_chain_)
2761 return;
2762 update_negotiation_needed_on_empty_chain_ = false;
2763 // Firing when chain is empty is only supported in Unified Plan to avoid Plan
2764 // B regressions. (In Plan B, onnegotiationneeded is already broken anyway, so
2765 // firing it even more might just be confusing.)
2766 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {

2797
2798void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UpdateNegotiationNeeded() {
2799 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2800 if (!IsUnifiedPlan()) {
2801 pc_->Observer()->OnRenegotiationNeeded();
2802 GenerateNegotiationNeededEvent();
2803 return;
2804 }
2805
2806 // In the spec, a task is queued here to run the following steps - this is
2807 // meant to ensure we do not fire onnegotiationneeded prematurely if multiple
2808 // changes are being made at once. In order to support Chromium's
2809 // implementation where the JavaScript representation of the PeerConnection
2810 // lives on a separate thread though, the queuing of a task is instead
2811 // performed by the PeerConnectionObserver posting from the signaling thread
2812 // to the JavaScript main thread that negotiation is needed. And because the
2813 // Operations Chain lives on the WebRTC signaling thread,
2814 // ShouldFireNegotiationNeededEvent() must be called before firing the event
2815 // to ensure the Operations Chain is still empty and the event has not been
2816 // invalidated.
2817
2818 // If connection's [[IsClosed]] slot is true, abort these steps.
2819 if (pc_->IsClosed())
2820 return;
2821
2822 // If connection's signaling state is not "stable", abort these steps.
2823 if (signaling_state() != PeerConnectionInterface::kStable)
2824 return;
2825
2826 // NOTE
2827 // The negotiation-needed flag will be updated once the state transitions to
2828 // "stable", as part of the steps for setting an RTCSessionDescription.
2829
2830 // If the result of checking if negotiation is needed is false, clear the
2831 // negotiation-needed flag by setting connection's [[NegotiationNeeded]] slot
2832 // to false, and abort these steps.
2833 bool is_negotiation_needed = CheckIfNegotiationIsNeeded();
2834 if (!is_negotiation_needed) {
2835 is_negotiation_needed_ = false;
2836 // Invalidate any negotiation needed event that may previosuly have been
2837 // generated.
2838 ++negotiation_needed_event_id_;
2839 return;
2840 }
2841
2842 // If connection's [[NegotiationNeeded]] slot is already true, abort these
2843 // steps.
2844 if (is_negotiation_needed_)
2845 return;
2846
2847 // Set connection's [[NegotiationNeeded]] slot to true.
2848 is_negotiation_needed_ = true;
2849
2850 // Queue a task that runs the following steps:
2851 // If connection's [[IsClosed]] slot is true, abort these steps.
2852 // If connection's [[NegotiationNeeded]] slot is false, abort these steps.
2853 // Fire an event named negotiationneeded at connection.
2854 pc_->Observer()->OnRenegotiationNeeded();
2855 // Fire the spec-compliant version; when ShouldFireNegotiationNeededEvent() is
2856 // used in the task queued by the observer, this event will only fire when the
2857 // chain is empty.
2858 GenerateNegotiationNeededEvent();
2859}
2860
2861bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::CheckIfNegotiationIsNeeded() {
2862 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2863 // 1. If any implementation-specific negotiation is required, as described at
2864 // the start of this section, return true.
2865
2866 // 2. If connection.[[LocalIceCredentialsToReplace]] is not empty, return
2867 // true.
2868 if (local_ice_credentials_to_replace_->HasIceCredentials()) {
2869 return true;
2870 }
2871
2872 // 3. Let description be connection.[[CurrentLocalDescription]].
2873 const SessionDescriptionInterface* description = current_local_description();
2874 if (!description)
2875 return true;
2876
2877 // 4. If connection has created any RTCDataChannels, and no m= section in
2878 // description has been negotiated yet for data, return true.
2879 if (data_channel_controller()->HasSctpDataChannels()) {
2880 if (!cricket::GetFirstDataContent(description->description()->contents()))
2881 return true;
2882 }
2883
2884 // 5. For each transceiver in connection's set of transceivers, perform the
2885 // following checks:
2886 for (const auto& transceiver : transceivers()->ListInternal()) {
2887 const ContentInfo* current_local_msection =
2888 FindTransceiverMSection(transceiver, description);
2889
2890 const ContentInfo* current_remote_msection =
2891 FindTransceiverMSection(transceiver, current_remote_description());
2892
2893 // 5.4 If transceiver is stopped and is associated with an m= section,
2894 // but the associated m= section is not yet rejected in
2895 // connection.[[CurrentLocalDescription]] or
2896 // connection.[[CurrentRemoteDescription]], return true.
2897 if (transceiver->stopped()) {
2898 RTC_DCHECK(transceiver->stopping());
2899 if (current_local_msection && !current_local_msection->rejected &&
2900 ((current_remote_msection && !current_remote_msection->rejected) ||
2901 !current_remote_msection)) {
2902 return true;
2903 }
2904 continue;
2905 }
2906
2907 // 5.1 If transceiver.[[Stopping]] is true and transceiver.[[Stopped]] is
2908 // false, return true.
2909 if (transceiver->stopping() && !transceiver->stopped())
2910 return true;
2911
2912 // 5.2 If transceiver isn't stopped and isn't yet associated with an m=
2913 // section in description, return true.
2914 if (!current_local_msection)
2915 return true;
2916
2917 const MediaContentDescription* current_local_media_description =
2918 current_local_msection->media_description();
2919 // 5.3 If transceiver isn't stopped and is associated with an m= section
2920 // in description then perform the following checks:
2921
2922 // 5.3.1 If transceiver.[[Direction]] is "sendrecv" or "sendonly", and the
2923 // associated m= section in description either doesn't contain a single
2924 // "a=msid" line, or the number of MSIDs from the "a=msid" lines in this
2925 // m= section, or the MSID values themselves, differ from what is in
2926 // transceiver.sender.[[AssociatedMediaStreamIds]], return true.
2927 if (RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(transceiver->direction())) {
2928 if (current_local_media_description->streams().size() == 0)
2929 return true;
2930
2931 std::vector<std::string> msection_msids;
2932 for (const auto& stream : current_local_media_description->streams()) {
2933 for (const std::string& msid : stream.stream_ids())
2934 msection_msids.push_back(msid);
2935 }
2936
2937 std::vector<std::string> transceiver_msids =
2938 transceiver->sender()->stream_ids();
2939 if (msection_msids.size() != transceiver_msids.size())
2940 return true;
2941
2942 absl::c_sort(transceiver_msids);
2943 absl::c_sort(msection_msids);
2944 if (transceiver_msids != msection_msids)
2945 return true;
2946 }
2947
2948 // 5.3.2 If description is of type "offer", and the direction of the
2949 // associated m= section in neither connection.[[CurrentLocalDescription]]
2950 // nor connection.[[CurrentRemoteDescription]] matches
2951 // transceiver.[[Direction]], return true.
2952 if (description->GetType() == SdpType::kOffer) {
2953 if (!current_remote_description())
2954 return true;
2955
2956 if (!current_remote_msection)
2957 return true;
2958
2959 RtpTransceiverDirection current_local_direction =
2960 current_local_media_description->direction();
2961 RtpTransceiverDirection current_remote_direction =
2962 current_remote_msection->media_description()->direction();
2963 if (transceiver->direction() != current_local_direction &&
2964 transceiver->direction() !=
2965 RtpTransceiverDirectionReversed(current_remote_direction)) {
2966 return true;
2967 }
2968 }
2969
2970 // 5.3.3 If description is of type "answer", and the direction of the
2971 // associated m= section in the description does not match
2972 // transceiver.[[Direction]] intersected with the offered direction (as
2973 // described in [JSEP] (section 5.3.1.)), return true.
2974 if (description->GetType() == SdpType::kAnswer) {
2975 if (!remote_description())
2976 return true;
2977
2978 const ContentInfo* offered_remote_msection =
2979 FindTransceiverMSection(transceiver, remote_description());
2980
2981 RtpTransceiverDirection offered_direction =
2982 offered_remote_msection
2983 ? offered_remote_msection->media_description()->direction()
2984 : RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive;
2985
2986 if (current_local_media_description->direction() !=
2987 (RtpTransceiverDirectionIntersection(
2988 transceiver->direction(),
2989 RtpTransceiverDirectionReversed(offered_direction)))) {
2990 return true;
2991 }
2992 }
2993 }
2994
2995 // If all the preceding checks were performed and true was not returned,
2996 // nothing remains to be negotiated; return false.
2997 return false;
2998}
2999
3000void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GenerateNegotiationNeededEvent() {
3001 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
3002 ++negotiation_needed_event_id_;
3003 pc_->Observer()->OnNegotiationNeededEvent(negotiation_needed_event_id_);
3004}
3005
3006RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ValidateSessionDescription(
3007 const SessionDescriptionInterface* sdesc,
3008 cricket::ContentSource source,
3009 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
3010 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
3011 if (session_error() != SessionError::kNone) {
3012 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, GetSessionErrorMsg());
3013 }
3014
3015 if (!sdesc || !sdesc->description()) {
3016 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, kInvalidSdp);
3017 }
3018
3019 SdpType type = sdesc->GetType();
3020 if ((source == cricket::CS_LOCAL && !ExpectSetLocalDescription(type)) ||
3021 (source == cricket::CS_REMOTE && !ExpectSetRemoteDescription(type))) {
3022 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
3023 RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
3024 "Called in wrong state: " + GetSignalingStateString(signaling_state()));
3025 }
3026
3027 RTCError error = ValidateMids(*sdesc->description());
3028 if (!error.ok()) {
3029 return error;
3030 }
3031
3032 // Verify crypto settings.
3033 std::string crypto_error;
3034 if (webrtc_session_desc_factory_->SdesPolicy() == cricket::SEC_REQUIRED ||
3035 pc_->dtls_enabled()) {
3036 RTCError crypto_error = VerifyCrypto(
3037 sdesc->description(), pc_->dtls_enabled(), bundle_groups_by_mid);
3038 if (!crypto_error.ok()) {
3039 return crypto_error;
3040 }
3041 }
3042
3043 // Verify ice-ufrag and ice-pwd.
3044 if (!VerifyIceUfragPwdPresent(sdesc->description(), bundle_groups_by_mid)) {
3045 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3046 kSdpWithoutIceUfragPwd);
3047 }
3048
3049 if (!pc_->ValidateBundleSettings(sdesc->description(),
3050 bundle_groups_by_mid)) {
3051 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3052 kBundleWithoutRtcpMux);
3053 }
3054
3055 // TODO(skvlad): When the local rtcp-mux policy is Require, reject any
3056 // m-lines that do not rtcp-mux enabled.
3057
3058 // Verify m-lines in Answer when compared against Offer.
3059 if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
3060 // With an answer we want to compare the new answer session description with
3061 // the offer's session description from the current negotiation.
3062 const cricket::SessionDescription* offer_desc =
3063 (source == cricket::CS_LOCAL) ? remote_description()->description()
3064 : local_description()->description();
3065 if (!MediaSectionsHaveSameCount(*offer_desc, *sdesc->description()) ||
3066 !MediaSectionsInSameOrder(*offer_desc, nullptr, *sdesc->description(),
3067 type)) {
3068 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3069 kMlineMismatchInAnswer);
3070 }
3071 } else {
3072 // The re-offers should respect the order of m= sections in current
3073 // description. See RFC3264 Section 8 paragraph 4 for more details.
3074 // With a re-offer, either the current local or current remote descriptions
3075 // could be the most up to date, so we would like to check against both of
3076 // them if they exist. It could be the case that one of them has a 0 port
3077 // for a media section, but the other does not. This is important to check
3078 // against in the case that we are recycling an m= section.
3079 const cricket::SessionDescription* current_desc = nullptr;
3080 const cricket::SessionDescription* secondary_current_desc = nullptr;
3081 if (local_description()) {
3082 current_desc = local_description()->description();
3083 if (remote_description()) {
3084 secondary_current_desc = remote_description()->description();
3085 }
3086 } else if (remote_description()) {
3087 current_desc = remote_description()->description();
3088 }
3089 if (current_desc &&
3090 !MediaSectionsInSameOrder(*current_desc, secondary_current_desc,
3091 *sdesc->description(), type)) {
3092 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3093 kMlineMismatchInSubsequentOffer);
3094 }
3095 }
3096
3097 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
3098 // Ensure that each audio and video media section has at most one
3099 // "StreamParams". This will return an error if receiving a session
3100 // description from a "Plan B" endpoint which adds multiple tracks of the
3101 // same type. With Unified Plan, there can only be at most one track per
3102 // media section.
3103 for (const ContentInfo& content : sdesc->description()->contents()) {
3104 const MediaContentDescription& desc = *content.media_description();
3105 if ((desc.type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
3106 desc.type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) &&
3107 desc.streams().size() > 1u) {
3108 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3109 "Media section has more than one track specified "
3110 "with a=ssrc lines which is not supported with "
3111 "Unified Plan.");
3112 }
3113 }
3114 }
3115
3116 return RTCError::OK();
3117}
3118
3119RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UpdateTransceiversAndDataChannels(
3120 cricket::ContentSource source,
3121 const SessionDescriptionInterface& new_session,
3122 const SessionDescriptionInterface* old_local_description,
3123 const SessionDescriptionInterface* old_remote_description,
3124 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
3125 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
3126 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
3127 RTC_DCHECK(IsUnifiedPlan());
3128
3129 if (new_session.GetType() == SdpType::kOffer) {
3130 // If the BUNDLE policy is max-bundle, then we know for sure that all
3131 // transports will be bundled from the start. Return an error if max-bundle
3132 // is specified but the session description does not have a BUNDLE group.
3133 if (pc_->configuration()->bundle_policy ==
3134 PeerConnectionInterface::kBundlePolicyMaxBundle &&
3135 bundle_groups_by_mid.empty()) {
3136 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3137 "max-bundle configured but session description "
3138 "has no BUNDLE group");
3139 }
3140 }
3141
3142 const ContentInfos& new_contents = new_session.description()->contents();
3143 for (size_t i = 0; i < new_contents.size(); ++i) {
3144 const cricket::ContentInfo& new_content = new_contents[i];
3145 cricket::MediaType media_type = new_content.media_description()->type();
3146 mid_generator_.AddKnownId(new_content.name);
3147 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(new_content.name);
3148 const cricket::ContentGroup* bundle_group =
3149 it != bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
3150 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
3151 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3152 const cricket::ContentInfo* old_local_content = nullptr;
3153 if (old_local_description &&
3154 i < old_local_description->description()->contents().size()) {
3155 old_local_content =
3156 &old_local_description->description()->contents()[i];
3157 }
3158 const cricket::ContentInfo* old_remote_content = nullptr;
3159 if (old_remote_description &&
3160 i < old_remote_description->description()->contents().size()) {
3161 old_remote_content =
3162 &old_remote_description->description()->contents()[i];
3163 }
3164 auto transceiver_or_error =
3165 AssociateTransceiver(source, new_session.GetType(), i, new_content,
3166 old_local_content, old_remote_content);
3167 if (!transceiver_or_error.ok()) {
3168 // In the case where a transceiver is rejected locally, we don't
3169 // expect to find a transceiver, but might find it in the case
3170 // where state is still "stopping", not "stopped".
3171 if (new_content.rejected) {
3172 continue;
3173 }
3174 return transceiver_or_error.MoveError();
3175 }
3176 auto transceiver = transceiver_or_error.MoveValue();
3177 RTCError error =
3178 UpdateTransceiverChannel(transceiver, new_content, bundle_group);
3179 if (!error.ok()) {
3180 return error;
3181 }
3182 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
3183 if (pc_->GetDataMid() && new_content.name != *(pc_->GetDataMid())) {
3184 // Ignore all but the first data section.
3185 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Ignoring data media section with MID="
3186 << new_content.name;
3187 continue;
3188 }
3189 RTCError error = UpdateDataChannel(source, new_content, bundle_group);
3190 if (!error.ok()) {
3191 return error;
3192 }
3193 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED) {
3194 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Ignoring unsupported media type";
3195 } else {
3196 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
3197 "Unknown section type.");
3198 }
3199 }
3200
3201 return RTCError::OK();
3202}

3204RTCErrorOr<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>>>
3205SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AssociateTransceiver(
3206 cricket::ContentSource source,
3207 SdpType type,
3208 size_t mline_index,
3209 const ContentInfo& content,
3210 const ContentInfo* old_local_content,
3211 const ContentInfo* old_remote_content) {
3212 RTC_DCHECK(IsUnifiedPlan());
3213#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
3214 // If this is an offer then the m= section might be recycled. If the m=
3215 // section is being recycled (defined as: rejected in the current local or
3216 // remote description and not rejected in new description), the transceiver
3217 // should have been removed by RemoveStoppedtransceivers()->
3218 if (IsMediaSectionBeingRecycled(type, content, old_local_content,

3222 ? old_local_content->name
3223 : old_remote_content->name;

3225 // The transceiver should be disassociated in RemoveStoppedTransceivers()
3226 RTC_DCHECK(!old_transceiver);
3227 }
3228#endif
3229
3230 const MediaContentDescription* media_desc = content.media_description();
3231 auto transceiver = transceivers()->FindByMid(content.name);
3232 if (source == cricket::CS_LOCAL) {
3233 // Find the RtpTransceiver that corresponds to this m= section, using the
3234 // mapping between transceivers and m= section indices established when
3235 // creating the offer.
3236 if (!transceiver) {
3237 transceiver = transceivers()->FindByMLineIndex(mline_index);
3238 }
3239 if (!transceiver) {

3241 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,

3246 // If the m= section is sendrecv or recvonly, and there are RtpTransceivers
3247 // of the same type...

3249 // AddTrack cannot be called to initialize it.
3250 if (!transceiver &&
3251 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(media_desc->direction()) &&

3256 // recvonly direction.
3257 if (!transceiver) {
3258 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Adding "
3259 << cricket::MediaTypeToString(media_desc->type())
3260 << " transceiver for MID=" << content.name
3261 << " at i=" << mline_index
3262 << " in response to the remote description.";

3265 GetSendEncodingsFromRemoteDescription(*media_desc);

3267 nullptr, {}, send_encodings);

3269 if (!media_desc->streams().empty()) {
3270 receiver_id = media_desc->streams()[0].id;
3271 } else {
3272 receiver_id = rtc::CreateRandomUuid();
3273 }
3274 auto receiver =
3275 rtp_manager()->CreateReceiver(media_desc->type(), receiver_id);
3276 transceiver = rtp_manager()->CreateAndAddTransceiver(sender, receiver);
3277 transceiver->internal()->set_direction(
3278 RtpTransceiverDirection::kRecvOnly);
3279 if (type == SdpType::kOffer) {
3280 transceivers()->StableState(transceiver)->set_newly_created();
3281 }
3282 }
3283
3284 RTC_DCHECK(transceiver);
3285
3286 // Check if the offer indicated simulcast but the answer rejected it.
3287 // This can happen when simulcast is not supported on the remote party.
3288 if (SimulcastIsRejected(old_local_content, *media_desc)) {
3289 RTC_HISTOGRAM_BOOLEAN(kSimulcastDisabled, true);
3290 RTCError error =
3291 DisableSimulcastInSender(transceiver->internal()->sender_internal());
3292 if (!error.ok()) {
3293 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to remove rejected simulcast.";
3294 return std::move(error);
3295 }
3296 }
3297 }
3298
3299 if (transceiver->media_type() != media_desc->type()) {
3300 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
3301 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
3302 "Transceiver type does not match media description type.");
3303 }
3304

3306 std::vector<SimulcastLayer> layers =
3307 source == cricket::CS_LOCAL
3308 ? media_desc->simulcast_description().send_layers().GetAllLayers()
3309 : media_desc->simulcast_description()
3310 .receive_layers()
3311 .GetAllLayers();
3312 RTCError error = UpdateSimulcastLayerStatusInSender(
3313 layers, transceiver->internal()->sender_internal());
3314 if (!error.ok()) {
3315 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed updating status for simulcast layers.";
3316 return std::move(error);
3317 }
3318 }
3319 if (type == SdpType::kOffer) {
3320 bool state_changes = transceiver->internal()->mid() != content.name ||
3321 transceiver->internal()->mline_index() != mline_index;
3322 if (state_changes) {
3323 transceivers()
3324 ->StableState(transceiver)
3325 ->SetMSectionIfUnset(transceiver->internal()->mid(),
3326 transceiver->internal()->mline_index());
3327 }
3328 }
3329 // Associate the found or created RtpTransceiver with the m= section by
3330 // setting the value of the RtpTransceiver's mid property to the MID of the m=
3331 // section, and establish a mapping between the transceiver and the index of
3332 // the m= section.
3333 transceiver->internal()->set_mid(content.name);
3334 transceiver->internal()->set_mline_index(mline_index);
3335 return std::move(transceiver);

3456rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>>
3457SdpOfferAnswerHandler::FindAvailableTransceiverToReceive(
3458 cricket::MediaType media_type) const {
3459 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
3460 RTC_DCHECK(IsUnifiedPlan());
3461 // From JSEP section 5.10 (Applying a Remote Description):
3462 // If the m= section is sendrecv or recvonly, and there are RtpTransceivers of
3463 // the same type that were added to the PeerConnection by addTrack and are not
3464 // associated with any m= section and are not stopped, find the first such
3465 // RtpTransceiver.
3466 for (auto transceiver : transceivers()->List()) {
3467 if (transceiver->media_type() == media_type &&
3468 transceiver->internal()->created_by_addtrack() && !transceiver->mid() &&
3469 !transceiver->stopped()) {
3470 return transceiver;
3471 }
3472 }
3473 return nullptr;
3474}

3476const cricket::ContentInfo*
3477SdpOfferAnswerHandler::FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(

3482 RTC_DCHECK(sdesc);

3484 if (!transceiver->mid()) {
3485 // This transceiver is not associated with a media section yet.
3486 return nullptr;

3489 } else {

3491 // first media section of that type.
3492 return cricket::GetFirstMediaContent(sdesc->description()->contents(),

3502

3533void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GetOptionsForPlanBOffer(
3534 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& offer_answer_options,
3535 cricket::MediaSessionOptions* session_options) {
3536 // Figure out transceiver directional preferences.
3537 bool send_audio =
3538 !rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver()->internal()->senders().empty();
3539 bool send_video =
3540 !rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver()->internal()->senders().empty();
3541
3542 // By default, generate sendrecv/recvonly m= sections.
3543 bool recv_audio = true;
3544 bool recv_video = true;
3545
3546 // By default, only offer a new m= section if we have media to send with it.
3547 bool offer_new_audio_description = send_audio;
3548 bool offer_new_video_description = send_video;
3549 bool offer_new_data_description =
3550 data_channel_controller()->HasDataChannels();
3551
3552 // The "offer_to_receive_X" options allow those defaults to be overridden.
3553 if (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_audio !=
3554 PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions::kUndefined) {
3555 recv_audio = (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_audio > 0);
3556 offer_new_audio_description =
3557 offer_new_audio_description ||
3558 (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_audio > 0);
3559 }
3560 if (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_video !=
3561 RTCOfferAnswerOptions::kUndefined) {
3562 recv_video = (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_video > 0);
3563 offer_new_video_description =
3564 offer_new_video_description ||
3565 (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_video > 0);
3566 }
3567
3568 absl::optional<size_t> audio_index;
3569 absl::optional<size_t> video_index;
3570 absl::optional<size_t> data_index;
3571 // If a current description exists, generate m= sections in the same order,
3572 // using the first audio/video/data section that appears and rejecting
3573 // extraneous ones.
3574 if (local_description()) {
3575 GenerateMediaDescriptionOptions(
3576 local_description(),
3577 RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(send_audio, recv_audio),
3578 RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(send_video, recv_video),
3579 &audio_index, &video_index, &data_index, session_options);
3580 }
3581
3582 // Add audio/video/data m= sections to the end if needed.
3583 if (!audio_index && offer_new_audio_description) {
3584 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions options(
3585 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, cricket::CN_AUDIO,
3586 RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(send_audio, recv_audio), false);
3587 options.header_extensions =
3588 channel_manager()->GetSupportedAudioRtpHeaderExtensions();
3589 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(options);
3590 audio_index = session_options->media_description_options.size() - 1;
3591 }
3592 if (!video_index && offer_new_video_description) {
3593 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions options(
3594 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, cricket::CN_VIDEO,
3595 RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(send_video, recv_video), false);
3596 options.header_extensions =
3597 channel_manager()->GetSupportedVideoRtpHeaderExtensions();
3598 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(options);
3599 video_index = session_options->media_description_options.size() - 1;
3600 }
3601 if (!data_index && offer_new_data_description) {
3602 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3603 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForActiveData(cricket::CN_DATA));
3604 data_index = session_options->media_description_options.size() - 1;
3605 }
3606
3607 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions* audio_media_description_options =
3608 !audio_index ? nullptr
3609 : &session_options->media_description_options[*audio_index];
3610 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions* video_media_description_options =
3611 !video_index ? nullptr
3612 : &session_options->media_description_options[*video_index];
3613
3614 AddPlanBRtpSenderOptions(rtp_manager()->GetSendersInternal(),
3615 audio_media_description_options,
3616 video_media_description_options,
3617 offer_answer_options.num_simulcast_layers);
3618}
3619
3620void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GetOptionsForUnifiedPlanOffer(
3621 const RTCOfferAnswerOptions& offer_answer_options,
3622 cricket::MediaSessionOptions* session_options) {
3623 // Rules for generating an offer are dictated by JSEP sections 5.2.1 (Initial
3624 // Offers) and 5.2.2 (Subsequent Offers).
3625 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(session_options->media_description_options.size(), 0);
3626 const ContentInfos no_infos;
3627 const ContentInfos& local_contents =
3628 (local_description() ? local_description()->description()->contents()
3629 : no_infos);
3630 const ContentInfos& remote_contents =
3631 (remote_description() ? remote_description()->description()->contents()
3632 : no_infos);
3633 // The mline indices that can be recycled. New transceivers should reuse these
3634 // slots first.
3635 std::queue<size_t> recycleable_mline_indices;
3636 // First, go through each media section that exists in either the local or
3637 // remote description and generate a media section in this offer for the
3638 // associated transceiver. If a media section can be recycled, generate a
3639 // default, rejected media section here that can be later overwritten.
3640 for (size_t i = 0;
3641 i < std::max(local_contents.size(), remote_contents.size()); ++i) {
3642 // Either |local_content| or |remote_content| is non-null.
3643 const ContentInfo* local_content =
3644 (i < local_contents.size() ? &local_contents[i] : nullptr);
3645 const ContentInfo* current_local_content =
3646 GetContentByIndex(current_local_description(), i);
3647 const ContentInfo* remote_content =
3648 (i < remote_contents.size() ? &remote_contents[i] : nullptr);
3649 const ContentInfo* current_remote_content =
3650 GetContentByIndex(current_remote_description(), i);
3651 bool had_been_rejected =
3652 (current_local_content && current_local_content->rejected) ||
3653 (current_remote_content && current_remote_content->rejected);
3654 const std::string& mid =
3655 (local_content ? local_content->name : remote_content->name);
3656 cricket::MediaType media_type =
3657 (local_content ? local_content->media_description()->type()
3658 : remote_content->media_description()->type());
3659 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
3660 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3661 // A media section is considered eligible for recycling if it is marked as
3662 // rejected in either the current local or current remote description.
3663 auto transceiver = transceivers()->FindByMid(mid);
3664 if (!transceiver) {
3665 // No associated transceiver. The media section has been stopped.
3666 recycleable_mline_indices.push(i);
3667 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3668 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(media_type, mid,
3669 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive,
3670 /*stopped=*/true));
3671 } else {
3672 // NOTE: a stopping transceiver should be treated as a stopped one in
3673 // createOffer as specified in
3674 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#dom-rtcpeerconnection-createoffer.
3675 if (had_been_rejected && transceiver->stopping()) {
3676 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3677 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(
3678 transceiver->media_type(), mid,
3679 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive,
3680 /*stopped=*/true));
3681 recycleable_mline_indices.push(i);
3682 } else {
3683 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3684 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForTransceiver(
3685 transceiver->internal(), mid,
3686 /*is_create_offer=*/true));
3687 // CreateOffer shouldn't really cause any state changes in
3688 // PeerConnection, but we need a way to match new transceivers to new
3689 // media sections in SetLocalDescription and JSEP specifies this is
3690 // done by recording the index of the media section generated for the
3691 // transceiver in the offer.
3692 transceiver->internal()->set_mline_index(i);
3693 }
3694 }
3695 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED) {
3696 RTC_DCHECK(local_content->rejected);
3697 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3698 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(media_type, mid,
3699 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive,
3700 /*stopped=*/true));
3701 } else {
3702 RTC_CHECK_EQ(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA, media_type);
3703 if (had_been_rejected) {
3704 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3705 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForRejectedData(mid));
3706 } else {
3707 RTC_CHECK(pc_->GetDataMid());
3708 if (mid == *(pc_->GetDataMid())) {
3709 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3710 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForActiveData(mid));
3711 } else {
3712 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3713 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForRejectedData(mid));
3714 }
3715 }
3716 }
3717 }
3718
3719 // Next, look for transceivers that are newly added (that is, are not stopped
3720 // and not associated). Reuse media sections marked as recyclable first,
3721 // otherwise append to the end of the offer. New media sections should be
3722 // added in the order they were added to the PeerConnection.
3723 for (const auto& transceiver : transceivers()->ListInternal()) {
3724 if (transceiver->mid() || transceiver->stopping()) {
3725 continue;
3726 }
3727 size_t mline_index;
3728 if (!recycleable_mline_indices.empty()) {
3729 mline_index = recycleable_mline_indices.front();
3730 recycleable_mline_indices.pop();
3731 session_options->media_description_options[mline_index] =
3732 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForTransceiver(
3733 transceiver, mid_generator_.GenerateString(),
3734 /*is_create_offer=*/true);
3735 } else {
3736 mline_index = session_options->media_description_options.size();
3737 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3738 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForTransceiver(
3739 transceiver, mid_generator_.GenerateString(),
3740 /*is_create_offer=*/true));
3741 }
3742 // See comment above for why CreateOffer changes the transceiver's state.
3743 transceiver->set_mline_index(mline_index);
3744 }
3745 // Lastly, add a m-section if we have local data channels and an m section
3746 // does not already exist.
3747 if (!pc_->GetDataMid() && data_channel_controller()->HasDataChannels()) {
3748 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3749 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForActiveData(
3750 mid_generator_.GenerateString()));
3751 }
3752}
3753
3754void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GetOptionsForAnswer(
3755 const RTCOfferAnswerOptions& offer_answer_options,
3756 cricket::MediaSessionOptions* session_options) {
3757 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
3758 ExtractSharedMediaSessionOptions(offer_answer_options, session_options);
3759
3760 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
3761 GetOptionsForUnifiedPlanAnswer(offer_answer_options, session_options);
3762 } else {
3763 GetOptionsForPlanBAnswer(offer_answer_options, session_options);
3764 }
3765
3766 // Apply ICE renomination flag.
3767 for (auto& options : session_options->media_description_options) {
3768 options.transport_options.enable_ice_renomination =
3769 pc_->configuration()->enable_ice_renomination;
3770 }
3771
3772 session_options->rtcp_cname = rtcp_cname_;
3773 session_options->crypto_options = pc_->GetCryptoOptions();
3774 session_options->pooled_ice_credentials =
3775 pc_->network_thread()->Invoke<std::vector<cricket::IceParameters>>(
3776 RTC_FROM_HERE,
3777 [this] { return port_allocator()->GetPooledIceCredentials(); });
3778}
3779
3780void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GetOptionsForPlanBAnswer(
3781 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& offer_answer_options,
3782 cricket::MediaSessionOptions* session_options) {
3783 // Figure out transceiver directional preferences.
3784 bool send_audio =
3785 !rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver()->internal()->senders().empty();
3786 bool send_video =
3787 !rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver()->internal()->senders().empty();
3788
3789 // By default, generate sendrecv/recvonly m= sections. The direction is also
3790 // restricted by the direction in the offer.
3791 bool recv_audio = true;
3792 bool recv_video = true;
3793
3794 // The "offer_to_receive_X" options allow those defaults to be overridden.
3795 if (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_audio !=
3796 RTCOfferAnswerOptions::kUndefined) {
3797 recv_audio = (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_audio > 0);
3798 }
3799 if (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_video !=
3800 RTCOfferAnswerOptions::kUndefined) {
3801 recv_video = (offer_answer_options.offer_to_receive_video > 0);
3802 }
3803
3804 absl::optional<size_t> audio_index;
3805 absl::optional<size_t> video_index;
3806 absl::optional<size_t> data_index;
3807
3808 // Generate m= sections that match those in the offer.
3809 // Note that mediasession.cc will handle intersection our preferred
3810 // direction with the offered direction.
3811 GenerateMediaDescriptionOptions(
3812 remote_description(),
3813 RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(send_audio, recv_audio),
3814 RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(send_video, recv_video), &audio_index,
3815 &video_index, &data_index, session_options);
3816
3817 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions* audio_media_description_options =
3818 !audio_index ? nullptr
3819 : &session_options->media_description_options[*audio_index];
3820 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions* video_media_description_options =
3821 !video_index ? nullptr
3822 : &session_options->media_description_options[*video_index];
3823
3824 AddPlanBRtpSenderOptions(rtp_manager()->GetSendersInternal(),
3825 audio_media_description_options,
3826 video_media_description_options,
3827 offer_answer_options.num_simulcast_layers);
3828}
3829
3830void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GetOptionsForUnifiedPlanAnswer(
3831 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& offer_answer_options,
3832 cricket::MediaSessionOptions* session_options) {
3833 // Rules for generating an answer are dictated by JSEP sections 5.3.1 (Initial
3834 // Answers) and 5.3.2 (Subsequent Answers).
3835 RTC_DCHECK(remote_description());
3836 RTC_DCHECK(remote_description()->GetType() == SdpType::kOffer);
3837 for (const ContentInfo& content :
3838 remote_description()->description()->contents()) {
3839 cricket::MediaType media_type = content.media_description()->type();
3840 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
3841 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3842 auto transceiver = transceivers()->FindByMid(content.name);
3843 if (transceiver) {
3844 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3845 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForTransceiver(
3846 transceiver->internal(), content.name,
3847 /*is_create_offer=*/false));
3848 } else {
3849 // This should only happen with rejected transceivers.
3850 RTC_DCHECK(content.rejected);
3851 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3852 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(media_type, content.name,
3853 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive,
3854 /*stopped=*/true));
3855 }
3856 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED) {
3857 RTC_DCHECK(content.rejected);
3858 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3859 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(media_type, content.name,
3860 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive,
3861 /*stopped=*/true));
3862 } else {
3863 RTC_CHECK_EQ(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA, media_type);
3864 // Reject all data sections if data channels are disabled.
3865 // Reject a data section if it has already been rejected.
3866 // Reject all data sections except for the first one.
3867 if (content.rejected || content.name != *(pc_->GetDataMid())) {
3868 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3869 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForRejectedData(content.name));
3870 } else {
3871 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
3872 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForActiveData(content.name));
3873 }
3874 }
3875 }
3876}

3909RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::HandleLegacyOfferOptions(
3910 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& options) {
3911 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
3912 RTC_DCHECK(IsUnifiedPlan());
3913
3914 if (options.offer_to_receive_audio == 0) {
3915 RemoveRecvDirectionFromReceivingTransceiversOfType(
3916 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO);
3917 } else if (options.offer_to_receive_audio == 1) {
3918 AddUpToOneReceivingTransceiverOfType(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO);
3919 } else if (options.offer_to_receive_audio > 1) {
3920 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER,
3921 "offer_to_receive_audio > 1 is not supported.");
3922 }
3923
3924 if (options.offer_to_receive_video == 0) {
3925 RemoveRecvDirectionFromReceivingTransceiversOfType(
3926 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
3927 } else if (options.offer_to_receive_video == 1) {
3928 AddUpToOneReceivingTransceiverOfType(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
3929 } else if (options.offer_to_receive_video > 1) {
3930 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER,
3931 "offer_to_receive_video > 1 is not supported.");
3932 }
3933
3934 return RTCError::OK();
3935}

3937void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::RemoveRecvDirectionFromReceivingTransceiversOfType(
3938 cricket::MediaType media_type) {
3939 for (const auto& transceiver : GetReceivingTransceiversOfType(media_type)) {
3940 RtpTransceiverDirection new_direction =
3941 RtpTransceiverDirectionWithRecvSet(transceiver->direction(), false);
3942 if (new_direction != transceiver->direction()) {
3943 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing " << cricket::MediaTypeToString(media_type)
3944 << " transceiver (MID="
3945 << transceiver->mid().value_or("<not set>") << ") from "
3946 << RtpTransceiverDirectionToString(
3947 transceiver->direction())
3948 << " to "
3949 << RtpTransceiverDirectionToString(new_direction)
3950 << " since CreateOffer specified offer_to_receive=0";
3951 transceiver->internal()->set_direction(new_direction);
3952 }
3953 }
3954}

3956void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::AddUpToOneReceivingTransceiverOfType(
3957 cricket::MediaType media_type) {
3958 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
3959 if (GetReceivingTransceiversOfType(media_type).empty()) {
3960 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
3961 << "Adding one recvonly " << cricket::MediaTypeToString(media_type)
3962 << " transceiver since CreateOffer specified offer_to_receive=1";
3963 RtpTransceiverInit init;
3964 init.direction = RtpTransceiverDirection::kRecvOnly;
3965 pc_->AddTransceiver(media_type, nullptr, init,
3966 /*update_negotiation_needed=*/false);
3967 }

4023
4024void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UpdateLocalSenders(
4025 const std::vector<cricket::StreamParams>& streams,
4026 cricket::MediaType media_type) {
4027 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4028 std::vector<RtpSenderInfo>* current_senders =
4029 rtp_manager()->GetLocalSenderInfos(media_type);
4030
4031 // Find removed tracks. I.e., tracks where the track id, stream id or ssrc
4032 // don't match the new StreamParam.
4033 for (auto sender_it = current_senders->begin();
4034 sender_it != current_senders->end();
4035 /* incremented manually */) {
4036 const RtpSenderInfo& info = *sender_it;
4037 const cricket::StreamParams* params =
4038 cricket::GetStreamBySsrc(streams, info.first_ssrc);
4039 if (!params || params->id != info.sender_id ||
4040 params->first_stream_id() != info.stream_id) {
4041 rtp_manager()->OnLocalSenderRemoved(info, media_type);
4042 sender_it = current_senders->erase(sender_it);
4043 } else {
4044 ++sender_it;
4045 }
4046 }
4047
4048 // Find new and active senders.
4049 for (const cricket::StreamParams& params : streams) {
4050 // The sync_label is the MediaStream label and the |stream.id| is the
4051 // sender id.
4052 const std::string& stream_id = params.first_stream_id();
4053 const std::string& sender_id = params.id;
4054 uint32_t ssrc = params.first_ssrc();
4055 const RtpSenderInfo* sender_info =
4056 rtp_manager()->FindSenderInfo(*current_senders, stream_id, sender_id);
4057 if (!sender_info) {
4058 current_senders->push_back(RtpSenderInfo(stream_id, sender_id, ssrc));
4059 rtp_manager()->OnLocalSenderAdded(current_senders->back(), media_type);
4060 }
4061 }
4062}
4063
4064void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UpdateRemoteSendersList(
4065 const cricket::StreamParamsVec& streams,
4066 bool default_sender_needed,
4067 cricket::MediaType media_type,
4068 StreamCollection* new_streams) {
4069 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4070 RTC_DCHECK(!IsUnifiedPlan());
4071
4072 std::vector<RtpSenderInfo>* current_senders =
4073 rtp_manager()->GetRemoteSenderInfos(media_type);
4074
4075 // Find removed senders. I.e., senders where the sender id or ssrc don't match
4076 // the new StreamParam.
4077 for (auto sender_it = current_senders->begin();
4078 sender_it != current_senders->end();
4079 /* incremented manually */) {
4080 const RtpSenderInfo& info = *sender_it;
4081 const cricket::StreamParams* params =
4082 cricket::GetStreamBySsrc(streams, info.first_ssrc);
4083 std::string params_stream_id;
4084 if (params) {
4085 params_stream_id =
4086 (!params->first_stream_id().empty() ? params->first_stream_id()
4087 : kDefaultStreamId);
4088 }
4089 bool sender_exists = params && params->id == info.sender_id &&
4090 params_stream_id == info.stream_id;
4091 // If this is a default track, and we still need it, don't remove it.
4092 if ((info.stream_id == kDefaultStreamId && default_sender_needed) ||
4093 sender_exists) {
4094 ++sender_it;
4095 } else {
4096 rtp_manager()->OnRemoteSenderRemoved(
4097 info, remote_streams_->find(info.stream_id), media_type);
4098 sender_it = current_senders->erase(sender_it);
4099 }
4100 }
4101
4102 // Find new and active senders.
4103 for (const cricket::StreamParams& params : streams) {
4104 if (!params.has_ssrcs()) {
4105 // The remote endpoint has streams, but didn't signal ssrcs. For an active
4106 // sender, this means it is coming from a Unified Plan endpoint,so we just
4107 // create a default.
4108 default_sender_needed = true;
4109 break;
4110 }
4111
4112 // |params.id| is the sender id and the stream id uses the first of
4113 // |params.stream_ids|. The remote description could come from a Unified
4114 // Plan endpoint, with multiple or no stream_ids() signaled. Since this is
4115 // not supported in Plan B, we just take the first here and create the
4116 // default stream ID if none is specified.
4117 const std::string& stream_id =
4118 (!params.first_stream_id().empty() ? params.first_stream_id()
4119 : kDefaultStreamId);
4120 const std::string& sender_id = params.id;
4121 uint32_t ssrc = params.first_ssrc();
4122
4123 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface> stream =
4124 remote_streams_->find(stream_id);
4125 if (!stream) {
4126 // This is a new MediaStream. Create a new remote MediaStream.
4127 stream = MediaStreamProxy::Create(rtc::Thread::Current(),
4128 MediaStream::Create(stream_id));
4129 remote_streams_->AddStream(stream);
4130 new_streams->AddStream(stream);
4131 }
4132
4133 const RtpSenderInfo* sender_info =
4134 rtp_manager()->FindSenderInfo(*current_senders, stream_id, sender_id);
4135 if (!sender_info) {
4136 current_senders->push_back(RtpSenderInfo(stream_id, sender_id, ssrc));
4137 rtp_manager()->OnRemoteSenderAdded(current_senders->back(), stream,
4138 media_type);
4139 }
4140 }
4141
4142 // Add default sender if necessary.
4143 if (default_sender_needed) {
4144 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface> default_stream =
4145 remote_streams_->find(kDefaultStreamId);
4146 if (!default_stream) {
4147 // Create the new default MediaStream.
4148 default_stream = MediaStreamProxy::Create(
4149 rtc::Thread::Current(), MediaStream::Create(kDefaultStreamId));
4150 remote_streams_->AddStream(default_stream);
4151 new_streams->AddStream(default_stream);
4152 }
4153 std::string default_sender_id = (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)
4154 ? kDefaultAudioSenderId
4155 : kDefaultVideoSenderId;
4156 const RtpSenderInfo* default_sender_info = rtp_manager()->FindSenderInfo(
4157 *current_senders, kDefaultStreamId, default_sender_id);
4158 if (!default_sender_info) {
4159 current_senders->push_back(
4160 RtpSenderInfo(kDefaultStreamId, default_sender_id, /*ssrc=*/0));
4161 rtp_manager()->OnRemoteSenderAdded(current_senders->back(),
4162 default_stream, media_type);
4163 }
4164 }
4165}

4176
4177RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::PushdownMediaDescription(
4178 SdpType type,
4179 cricket::ContentSource source,
4180 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
4181 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
4182 const SessionDescriptionInterface* sdesc =
4183 (source == cricket::CS_LOCAL ? local_description()
4184 : remote_description());
4185 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4186 RTC_DCHECK(sdesc);
4187
4188 if (!UpdatePayloadTypeDemuxingState(source, bundle_groups_by_mid)) {
4189 // Note that this is never expected to fail, since RtpDemuxer doesn't return
4190 // an error when changing payload type demux criteria, which is all this
4191 // does.
4192 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
4193 "Failed to update payload type demuxing state.");
4194 }
4195
4196 // Push down the new SDP media section for each audio/video transceiver.
4197 auto rtp_transceivers = transceivers()->ListInternal();
4198 std::vector<
4199 std::pair<cricket::ChannelInterface*, const MediaContentDescription*>>
4200 channels;
4201 for (const auto& transceiver : rtp_transceivers) {
4202 const ContentInfo* content_info =
4203 FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(transceiver, sdesc);
4204 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->channel();
4205 if (!channel || !content_info || content_info->rejected) {
4206 continue;
4207 }
4208 const MediaContentDescription* content_desc =
4209 content_info->media_description();
4210 if (!content_desc) {
4211 continue;
4212 }
4213
4214 transceiver->OnNegotiationUpdate(type, content_desc);
4215 channels.push_back(std::make_pair(channel, content_desc));
4216 }
4217
4218 if (!channels.empty()) {
4219 RTCError error =
4220 pc_->worker_thread()->Invoke<RTCError>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&]() {
4221 std::string error;
4222 for (const auto& entry : channels) {
4223 bool success =
4224 (source == cricket::CS_LOCAL)
4225 ? entry.first->SetLocalContent(entry.second, type, &error)
4226 : entry.first->SetRemoteContent(entry.second, type, &error);
4227 if (!success) {
4228 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, error);
4229 }
4230 }
4231 return RTCError::OK();
4232 });
4233 if (!error.ok()) {
4234 return error;
4235 }
4236 }
4237
4238 // Need complete offer/answer with an SCTP m= section before starting SCTP,
4239 // according to https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp-19
4240 if (pc_->sctp_mid() && local_description() && remote_description()) {
4241 auto local_sctp_description = cricket::GetFirstSctpDataContentDescription(
4242 local_description()->description());
4243 auto remote_sctp_description = cricket::GetFirstSctpDataContentDescription(
4244 remote_description()->description());
4245 if (local_sctp_description && remote_sctp_description) {
4246 int max_message_size;
4247 // A remote max message size of zero means "any size supported".
4248 // We configure the connection with our own max message size.
4249 if (remote_sctp_description->max_message_size() == 0) {
4250 max_message_size = local_sctp_description->max_message_size();
4251 } else {
4252 max_message_size =
4253 std::min(local_sctp_description->max_message_size(),
4254 remote_sctp_description->max_message_size());
4255 }
4256 pc_->StartSctpTransport(local_sctp_description->port(),
4257 remote_sctp_description->port(),
4258 max_message_size);
4259 }
4260 }
4261
4262 return RTCError::OK();
4263}

4265RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::PushdownTransportDescription(
4266 cricket::ContentSource source,
4267 SdpType type) {
4268 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4269
4270 if (source == cricket::CS_LOCAL) {
4271 const SessionDescriptionInterface* sdesc = local_description();
4272 RTC_DCHECK(sdesc);
4273 return transport_controller()->SetLocalDescription(type,
4274 sdesc->description());
4275 } else {
4276 const SessionDescriptionInterface* sdesc = remote_description();
4277 RTC_DCHECK(sdesc);
4278 return transport_controller()->SetRemoteDescription(type,
4279 sdesc->description());
4280 }
4281}
4282
4283void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::RemoveStoppedTransceivers() {
4284 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4285 // 3.2.10.1: For each transceiver in the connection's set of transceivers
4286 // run the following steps:
4287 if (!IsUnifiedPlan())
4288 return;
4289 // Traverse a copy of the transceiver list.
4290 auto transceiver_list = transceivers()->List();
4291 for (auto transceiver : transceiver_list) {
4292 // 3.2.10.1.1: If transceiver is stopped, associated with an m= section
4293 // and the associated m= section is rejected in
4294 // connection.[[CurrentLocalDescription]] or
4295 // connection.[[CurrentRemoteDescription]], remove the
4296 // transceiver from the connection's set of transceivers.
4297 if (!transceiver->stopped()) {
4298 continue;
4299 }
4300 const ContentInfo* local_content = FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(
4301 transceiver->internal(), local_description());
4302 const ContentInfo* remote_content = FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(
4303 transceiver->internal(), remote_description());
4304 if ((local_content && local_content->rejected) ||
4305 (remote_content && remote_content->rejected)) {
4306 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Dissociating transceiver"
4307 " since the media section is being recycled.";
4308 transceiver->internal()->set_mid(absl::nullopt);
4309 transceiver->internal()->set_mline_index(absl::nullopt);
4310 } else if (!local_content && !remote_content) {
4311 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11973): Consider if this should be removed already
4312 // See https://github.com/w3c/webrtc-pc/issues/2576
4313 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
4314 << "Dropping stopped transceiver that was never associated";
4315 }
4316 transceivers()->Remove(transceiver);
4317 }
4318}

4320void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::RemoveUnusedChannels(
4321 const SessionDescription* desc) {
4322 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4323 // Destroy video channel first since it may have a pointer to the
4324 // voice channel.
4325 const cricket::ContentInfo* video_info = cricket::GetFirstVideoContent(desc);
4326 if (!video_info || video_info->rejected) {
4327 DestroyTransceiverChannel(rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver());
4328 }
4329
4330 const cricket::ContentInfo* audio_info = cricket::GetFirstAudioContent(desc);
4331 if (!audio_info || audio_info->rejected) {
4332 DestroyTransceiverChannel(rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver());
4333 }
4334
4335 const cricket::ContentInfo* data_info = cricket::GetFirstDataContent(desc);
4336 if (!data_info || data_info->rejected) {
4337 DestroyDataChannelTransport();
4338 }
4339}

4341void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ReportNegotiatedSdpSemantics(
4342 const SessionDescriptionInterface& answer) {
4343 SdpSemanticNegotiated semantics_negotiated;
4344 switch (answer.description()->msid_signaling()) {
4345 case 0:
4346 semantics_negotiated = kSdpSemanticNegotiatedNone;
4347 break;
4348 case cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection:
4349 semantics_negotiated = kSdpSemanticNegotiatedUnifiedPlan;
4350 break;
4351 case cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute:
4352 semantics_negotiated = kSdpSemanticNegotiatedPlanB;
4353 break;
4354 case cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection |
4355 cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute:
4356 semantics_negotiated = kSdpSemanticNegotiatedMixed;
4357 break;
4358 default:
4359 RTC_NOTREACHED();
4360 }
4361 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.SdpSemanticNegotiated",
4362 semantics_negotiated, kSdpSemanticNegotiatedMax);
4363}

4380
4381bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UseCandidatesInSessionDescription(
4382 const SessionDescriptionInterface* remote_desc) {
4383 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4384 if (!remote_desc) {
4385 return true;
4386 }
4387 bool ret = true;
4388
4389 for (size_t m = 0; m < remote_desc->number_of_mediasections(); ++m) {
4390 const IceCandidateCollection* candidates = remote_desc->candidates(m);
4391 for (size_t n = 0; n < candidates->count(); ++n) {
4392 const IceCandidateInterface* candidate = candidates->at(n);
4393 bool valid = false;
4394 if (!ReadyToUseRemoteCandidate(candidate, remote_desc, &valid)) {
4395 if (valid) {
4396 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
4397 << "UseCandidatesInSessionDescription: Not ready to use "
4398 "candidate.";
4399 }
4400 continue;
4401 }
4402 ret = UseCandidate(candidate);
4403 if (!ret) {
4404 break;
4405 }
4406 }
4407 }
4408 return ret;
4409}
4410
4411bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UseCandidate(
4412 const IceCandidateInterface* candidate) {
4413 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4414
4415 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
4416
4417 RTCErrorOr<const cricket::ContentInfo*> result =
4418 FindContentInfo(remote_description(), candidate);
4419 if (!result.ok())
4420 return false;
4421
4422 const cricket::Candidate& c = candidate->candidate();
4423 RTCError error = cricket::VerifyCandidate(c);
4424 if (!error.ok()) {
4425 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid candidate: " << c.ToString();
4426 return true;
4427 }
4428
4429 pc_->AddRemoteCandidate(result.value()->name, c);
4430
4431 return true;
4432}
4433
4434// We need to check the local/remote description for the Transport instead of
4435// the session, because a new Transport added during renegotiation may have
4436// them unset while the session has them set from the previous negotiation.
4437// Not doing so may trigger the auto generation of transport description and
4438// mess up DTLS identity information, ICE credential, etc.
4439bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::ReadyToUseRemoteCandidate(
4440 const IceCandidateInterface* candidate,
4441 const SessionDescriptionInterface* remote_desc,
4442 bool* valid) {
4443 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4444 *valid = true;
4445
4446 const SessionDescriptionInterface* current_remote_desc =
4447 remote_desc ? remote_desc : remote_description();
4448
4449 if (!current_remote_desc) {
4450 return false;
4451 }
4452
4453 RTCErrorOr<const cricket::ContentInfo*> result =
4454 FindContentInfo(current_remote_desc, candidate);
4455 if (!result.ok()) {
4456 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "ReadyToUseRemoteCandidate: Invalid candidate. "
4457 << result.error().message();
4458
4459 *valid = false;
4460 return false;
4461 }
4462
4463 return true;
4464}
4465
4466RTCErrorOr<const cricket::ContentInfo*> SdpOfferAnswerHandler::FindContentInfo(
4467 const SessionDescriptionInterface* description,
4468 const IceCandidateInterface* candidate) {
4469 if (!candidate->sdp_mid().empty()) {
4470 auto& contents = description->description()->contents();
4471 auto it = absl::c_find_if(
4472 contents, [candidate](const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info) {
4473 return content_info.mid() == candidate->sdp_mid();
4474 });
4475 if (it == contents.end()) {
4476 return RTCError(
4477 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
4478 "Mid " + candidate->sdp_mid() +
4479 " specified but no media section with that mid found.");
4480 } else {
4481 return &*it;
4482 }
4483 } else if (candidate->sdp_mline_index() >= 0) {
4484 size_t mediacontent_index =
4485 static_cast<size_t>(candidate->sdp_mline_index());
4486 size_t content_size = description->description()->contents().size();
4487 if (mediacontent_index < content_size) {
4488 return &description->description()->contents()[mediacontent_index];
4489 } else {
4490 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_RANGE,
4491 "Media line index (" +
4492 rtc::ToString(candidate->sdp_mline_index()) +
4493 ") out of range (number of mlines: " +
4494 rtc::ToString(content_size) + ").");
4495 }
4496 }
4497
4498 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
4499 "Neither sdp_mline_index nor sdp_mid specified.");
4500}

4502RTCError SdpOfferAnswerHandler::CreateChannels(const SessionDescription& desc) {
4503 // Creating the media channels. Transports should already have been created
4504 // at this point.
4505 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4506 const cricket::ContentInfo* voice = cricket::GetFirstAudioContent(&desc);
4507 if (voice && !voice->rejected &&
4508 !rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver()->internal()->channel()) {
4509 cricket::VoiceChannel* voice_channel = CreateVoiceChannel(voice->name);
4510 if (!voice_channel) {
4511 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
4512 "Failed to create voice channel.");
4513 }
4514 rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver()->internal()->SetChannel(voice_channel);
4515 }
4516
4517 const cricket::ContentInfo* video = cricket::GetFirstVideoContent(&desc);
4518 if (video && !video->rejected &&
4519 !rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver()->internal()->channel()) {
4520 cricket::VideoChannel* video_channel = CreateVideoChannel(video->name);
4521 if (!video_channel) {
4522 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
4523 "Failed to create video channel.");
4524 }
4525 rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver()->internal()->SetChannel(video_channel);
4526 }
4527
4528 const cricket::ContentInfo* data = cricket::GetFirstDataContent(&desc);
4529 if (data && !data->rejected &&
4530 !data_channel_controller()->data_channel_transport()) {
4531 if (!CreateDataChannel(data->name)) {
4532 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
4533 "Failed to create data channel2.");
4534 }
4535 }
4536
4537 return RTCError::OK();
4538}

4595void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DestroyTransceiverChannel(
4596 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>>
4597 transceiver) {
4598 RTC_DCHECK(transceiver);
4599 RTC_LOG_THREAD_BLOCK_COUNT();
4600
4601 // TODO(tommi): We're currently on the signaling thread.
4602 // There are multiple hops to the worker ahead.
4603 // Consider if we can make the call to SetChannel() on the worker thread
4604 // (and require that to be the context it's always called in) and also
4605 // call DestroyChannelInterface there, since it also needs to hop to the
4606 // worker.
4607
4608 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->internal()->channel();
4609 RTC_DCHECK_BLOCK_COUNT_NO_MORE_THAN(0);
4610 if (channel) {
4611 // TODO(tommi): VideoRtpReceiver::SetMediaChannel blocks and jumps to the

4674 // TODO(tommi): Figure out why we can get 2 blocking calls when running

4681void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::DestroyAllChannels() {
4682 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4683 if (!transceivers()) {
4684 return;
4685 }
4686
4687 RTC_LOG_THREAD_BLOCK_COUNT();
4688
4689 // Destroy video channels first since they may have a pointer to a voice
4690 // channel.
4691 auto list = transceivers()->List();
4692 RTC_DCHECK_BLOCK_COUNT_NO_MORE_THAN(0);
4693
4694 for (const auto& transceiver : list) {

4699 for (const auto& transceiver : list) {

4707
4708void SdpOfferAnswerHandler::GenerateMediaDescriptionOptions(
4709 const SessionDescriptionInterface* session_desc,
4710 RtpTransceiverDirection audio_direction,
4711 RtpTransceiverDirection video_direction,
4712 absl::optional<size_t>* audio_index,
4713 absl::optional<size_t>* video_index,
4714 absl::optional<size_t>* data_index,
4715 cricket::MediaSessionOptions* session_options) {
4716 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4717 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content :
4718 session_desc->description()->contents()) {
4719 if (IsAudioContent(&content)) {
4720 // If we already have an audio m= section, reject this extra one.
4721 if (*audio_index) {
4722 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4723 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(
4724 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, content.name,
4725 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive, /*stopped=*/true));
4726 } else {
4727 bool stopped = (audio_direction == RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive);
4728 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4729 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
4730 content.name, audio_direction,
4731 stopped));
4732 *audio_index = session_options->media_description_options.size() - 1;
4733 }
4734 session_options->media_description_options.back().header_extensions =
4735 channel_manager()->GetSupportedAudioRtpHeaderExtensions();
4736 } else if (IsVideoContent(&content)) {
4737 // If we already have an video m= section, reject this extra one.
4738 if (*video_index) {
4739 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4740 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(
4741 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, content.name,
4742 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive, /*stopped=*/true));
4743 } else {
4744 bool stopped = (video_direction == RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive);
4745 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4746 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO,
4747 content.name, video_direction,
4748 stopped));
4749 *video_index = session_options->media_description_options.size() - 1;
4750 }
4751 session_options->media_description_options.back().header_extensions =
4752 channel_manager()->GetSupportedVideoRtpHeaderExtensions();
4753 } else if (IsUnsupportedContent(&content)) {
4754 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4755 cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED,
4756 content.name,
4757 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive,
4758 /*stopped=*/true));
4759 } else {
4760 RTC_DCHECK(IsDataContent(&content));
4761 // If we already have an data m= section, reject this extra one.
4762 if (*data_index) {
4763 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4764 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForRejectedData(content.name));
4765 } else {
4766 session_options->media_description_options.push_back(
4767 GetMediaDescriptionOptionsForActiveData(content.name));
4768 *data_index = session_options->media_description_options.size() - 1;
4769 }
4770 }
4771 }
4772}

4777 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
