4795
4796bool SdpOfferAnswerHandler::UpdatePayloadTypeDemuxingState(
4797 cricket::ContentSource source,
4798 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
4799 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
4800 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
4801 // We may need to delete any created default streams and disable creation of
4802 // new ones on the basis of payload type. This is needed to avoid SSRC
4803 // collisions in Call's RtpDemuxer, in the case that a transceiver has
4804 // created a default stream, and then some other channel gets the SSRC
4805 // signaled in the corresponding Unified Plan "m=" section. Specifically, we
4806 // need to disable payload type based demuxing when two bundled "m=" sections
4807 // are using the same payload type(s). For more context
4808 // see https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=11477
4809 const SessionDescriptionInterface* sdesc =
4810 (source == cricket::CS_LOCAL ? local_description()
4811 : remote_description());
4812 struct PayloadTypes {
4813 std::set<int> audio_payload_types;
4814 std::set<int> video_payload_types;
4815 bool pt_demuxing_enabled_audio = true;
4816 bool pt_demuxing_enabled_video = true;
4817 };
4818 std::map<const cricket::ContentGroup*, PayloadTypes> payload_types_by_bundle;
4819 for (auto& content_info : sdesc->description()->contents()) {
4820 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_info.name);
4821 const cricket::ContentGroup* bundle_group =
4822 it != bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
4823 // If this m= section isn't bundled, it's safe to demux by payload type
4824 // since other m= sections using the same payload type will also be using
4825 // different transports.
4826 if (!bundle_group) {
4827 continue;
4828 }
4829 PayloadTypes* payload_types = &payload_types_by_bundle[bundle_group];
4830 if (content_info.rejected ||
4831 (source == cricket::ContentSource::CS_LOCAL &&
4832 !RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(
4833 content_info.media_description()->direction())) ||
4834 (source == cricket::ContentSource::CS_REMOTE &&
4835 !RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(
4836 content_info.media_description()->direction()))) {
4837 // Ignore transceivers that are not receiving.
4838 continue;
4839 }
4840 switch (content_info.media_description()->type()) {
4841 case cricket::MediaType::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO: {
4842 const cricket::AudioContentDescription* audio_desc =
4843 content_info.media_description()->as_audio();
4844 for (const cricket::AudioCodec& audio : audio_desc->codecs()) {
4845 if (payload_types->audio_payload_types.count(audio.id)) {
4846 // Two m= sections are using the same payload type, thus demuxing
4847 // by payload type is not possible.
4848 payload_types->pt_demuxing_enabled_audio = false;
4849 }
4850 payload_types->audio_payload_types.insert(audio.id);
4851 }
4852 break;
4853 }
4854 case cricket::MediaType::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO: {
4855 const cricket::VideoContentDescription* video_desc =
4856 content_info.media_description()->as_video();
4857 for (const cricket::VideoCodec& video : video_desc->codecs()) {
4858 if (payload_types->video_payload_types.count(video.id)) {
4859 // Two m= sections are using the same payload type, thus demuxing
4860 // by payload type is not possible.
4861 payload_types->pt_demuxing_enabled_video = false;
4862 }
4863 payload_types->video_payload_types.insert(video.id);
4864 }
4865 break;
4866 }
4867 default:
4868 // Ignore data channels.
4869 continue;
4870 }
4871 }
4872
4873 // Gather all updates ahead of time so that all channels can be updated in a
4874 // single Invoke; necessary due to thread guards.
4875 std::vector<std::pair<RtpTransceiverDirection, cricket::ChannelInterface*>>
4876 channels_to_update;
4877 for (const auto& transceiver : transceivers()->ListInternal()) {
4878 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->channel();
4879 const ContentInfo* content =
4880 FindMediaSectionForTransceiver(transceiver, sdesc);
4881 if (!channel || !content) {
4882 continue;
4883 }
4884 RtpTransceiverDirection local_direction =
4885 content->media_description()->direction();
4886 if (source == cricket::CS_REMOTE) {
4887 local_direction = RtpTransceiverDirectionReversed(local_direction);
4888 }
4889 channels_to_update.emplace_back(local_direction, transceiver->channel());
4890 }
4891
4892 if (channels_to_update.empty()) {
4893 return true;
4894 }
4895 return pc_->worker_thread()->Invoke<bool>(
4896 RTC_FROM_HERE,
4897 [&channels_to_update, &bundle_groups_by_mid, &payload_types_by_bundle]() {
4898 for (const auto& it : channels_to_update) {
4899 RtpTransceiverDirection local_direction = it.first;
4900 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = it.second;
4901 cricket::MediaType media_type = channel->media_type();
4902 auto bundle_it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(channel->content_name());
4903 const cricket::ContentGroup* bundle_group =
4904 bundle_it != bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? bundle_it->second
4905 : nullptr;
4906 if (media_type == cricket::MediaType::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
4907 if (!channel->SetPayloadTypeDemuxingEnabled(
4908 (!bundle_group || payload_types_by_bundle[bundle_group]
4909 .pt_demuxing_enabled_audio) &&
4910 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(local_direction))) {
4911 return false;
4912 }
4913 } else if (media_type == cricket::MediaType::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
4914 if (!channel->SetPayloadTypeDemuxingEnabled(
4915 (!bundle_group || payload_types_by_bundle[bundle_group]
4916 .pt_demuxing_enabled_video) &&
4917 RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(local_direction))) {
4918 return false;
4919 }
4920 }
4921 }
4922 return true;
4923 });
4924}
